 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureArrangement : MonoBehaviour
{
    public GameObject[] Models = new GameObject[5];

    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Find and destroy existing furniture
        foreach (var model in new string[] { "Model_0", "Model_1", "Model_2", "Model_3", "Model_4" })
        {
            GameObject.Destroy(GameObject.Find(model));
        }

        // Step 2: Load new material for the plane
        GameObject.Find("Plane").GetComponent<Renderer>().material = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");

        // Step 3: Load and position new furniture
        GameObject desk = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk"), Vector3.zero, Quaternion.identity);
        desk.name = "Model_0";
        desk.transform.position = new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f);

        GameObject chair1 = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"), Vector3.zero, Quaternion.identity);
        chair1.name = "Model_1";
        chair1.transform.position = new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f);

        GameObject table = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table"), Vector3.zero, Quaternion.identity);
        table.name = "Model_2";
        table.transform.position = new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f);

        GameObject chair2 = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"), Vector3.zero, Quaternion.identity);
        chair2.name = "Model_3";
        chair2.transform.position = new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f);

        GameObject chair3 = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"), Vector3.zero, Quaternion.identity);
        chair3.name = "Model_4";
        chair3.transform.position = new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f);
        chair3.transform.rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0f, -97.34f, 0f);

        // Step 4: Add colliders
        foreach (var model in Models)
        {
            model.AddComponent<Collider>();
        }
    }
}

 using UnityEngine;
using System.Collections;

public class ReplaceModels : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Destroy existing models
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_0"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_1"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_2"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_3"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_4"));

        // Step 2: Change Plane's material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");

        // Step 3: Load and place new models
        GameObject desk = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk"));
        desk.name = "Model_0";
        desk.transform.position = new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f);

        chair1.name = "Model_1";

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using UnityEngine;
using System.Collections;

public class FurnitureLoader : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Find and destroy existing objects called 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++)
        {
            GameObject objectToDestroy = GameObject.Find("Model_" + i);
            if (objectToDestroy != null)
                Destroy(objectToDestroy);
        }

        // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' game object and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newPlaneMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            if (newPlaneMaterial != null)
                plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newPlaneMaterial;
        }

        // Step 3: Substitute the existing objects with objects loaded from the Furniture folder
        GameObject furnitureObject;
        Vector3 position;
        Quaternion rotation = Quaternion.identity;

        furnitureObject = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        position = new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f);
        GameObject newModel_0 = Instantiate(furnitureObject, position, Quaternion.identity);
        newModel_0.name = "Model_0";

        furnitureObject = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        position = new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f);
        GameObject newModel_1 = Instantiate(furnitureObject, position, Quaternion.identity);
        newModel_1.name = "Model_1";

        furnitureObject = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        position = new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f);
        GameObject newModel_2 = Instantiate(furnitureObject, position, Quaternion.identity);
        newModel_2.name = "Model_2";

        furnitureObject = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        position = new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f);
        GameObject newModel_3 = Instantiate(furnitureObject, position, Quaternion.identity);
        newModel_3.name = "Model_3";

        furnitureObject = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        position = new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f);
        rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0);
        GameObject newModel_4 = Instantiate(furnitureObject, position, rotation);
        newModel_4.name = "Model_4";

        // Step 4: Add a simple collider for every object
        foreach (GameObject obj in GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithTag("Furniture"))
        {
            if (obj.GetComponent<Collider>() == null)
                obj.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        }
    }
}

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using UnityEngine;
using System.Collections;

public class ReplaceModels : MonoBehaviour
{
    public void Start()
    {
        // 1) Find and destroy objects called 'Model_0', 'Model_1', 'Model_2', 'Model_3', 'Model_4'
        for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++)
        {
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find("Model_" + i);
            if (model != null)
            {
                DestroyImmediate(model);
            }
        }

        // 2) Find the 'Plane' gameobject and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        }

        // 3) Load and instantiate objects from the Furniture folder
        GameObject[] furniture = new GameObject[5];
        for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++)
        {
            string name = "Furniture/";
            switch (i)
            {
                case 0:
                    name += "Desk";
                    break;
                case 1:
                case 3:
                    name += "Chair";
                    break;
                case 2:
                    name += "Table";
                    break;
            }
            furniture[i] = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>(name), transform);
            furniture[i].name = "Model_" + i;
            switch (i)
            {
                case 0:
                    furniture[i].transform.position = new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f);
                    break;
                case 1:
                    furniture[i].transform.position = new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f);
                    break;
                case 2:
                    furniture[i].transform.position = new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f);
                    break;
                case 3:
                    furniture[i].transform.position = new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f);
                    break;
                case 4:
                    furniture[i].transform.position = new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f);
                    furniture[i].transform.Rotate(new Vector3(0, -97.34f, 0));
                    break;
            }
        }

        // 4) Add colliders to objects
        for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++)
        {
            furniture[i].AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        }
    }
}

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureLoader : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Find and destroy objects called 'Model_0', 'Model_1', 'Model_2', 'Model_3', and 'Model_4'
        GameObject[] models = GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithTag("Furniture");
        foreach (GameObject model in models)
        {
            Destroy(model);
        }

        // Find the gameobject called 'Plane' and change its material with the following code: Resources.Load<Material>(Furniture/Material)
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material furnitureMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = furnitureMaterial;

        // Substitute them with objects loaded from the Furniture folder, and rename them 'Model_0', 'Model_1', 'Model_2' 'Model_3 'Model_4'
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        GameObject chair = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        GameObject chair2 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair2");

        desk.name = "Model_0";
        table.name = "Model_1";
        chair.name = "Model_2";
        chair2.name = "Model_3";

        // Set the position and rotation of each object
        desk.transform.position = new Vector3(-0.47f, 0.08f, 7.13f);
        table.transform.position = new Vector3(-2.64f, 0.08f, 4.62f);
        chair.transform.position = new Vector3(-2.76f, 0.08f, 6.28f);
        chair2.transform.position = new Vector3(-4.37f, 0.08f, 4.81f);

        chair2.transform.rotation = Quaternion.Euler(new Vector3(0f, -97.34f, 0f));

        // Add a simple collider for each object
        desk.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        table.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        chair.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        chair2.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
    }
}

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureLoader : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Destroy objects called 'Model_0', 'Model_1', 'Model_2', and 'Model_3'
        GameObject[] models = GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithTag("Model");
        foreach (GameObject model in models)
        {
            Destroy(model);
        }

        // Step 2: Change the material of the gameobject called 'Plane' to a material loaded from the Furniture folder
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material furnitureMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = furnitureMaterial;

        // Step 3: Substitute the gameobjects 'Desk', 'Table', 'Chair' and 'Chair' with objects loaded from the Furniture folder
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load("Furniture/Table");
        GameObject chair0 = Resources.Load("Furniture/Chair");
        GameObject chair1 = Resources.Load("Furniture/Chair");
        desk.name = "Model_0";
        table.name = "Model_1";
        chair0.name = "Model_2";
        chair1.name = "Model_3";
        GameObject[] furnitureObjects = new GameObject[] { desk, table, chair0, chair1 };
        foreach (GameObject furnitureObject in furnitureObjects)
        {
            furnitureObject.transform.parent = plane.transform;
        }

        // Step 4: Add simple colliders for every object
        foreach (GameObject obj in furnitureObjects)
        {
            BoxCollider boxCollider = obj.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            Rigidbody rb = obj.GetComponent<Rigidbody>();
            if (rb == null)
            {
                rb = obj.AddComponent<Rigidbody>();
            }
        }
    }
}
Elapsed time for the generation of the script took 18,59454 seconds

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureLoader : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Destroy objects called 'Model_0', 'Model_1', 'Model_2', and 'Model_3'
        GameObject[] models = GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithTag("Model");
        foreach (GameObject model in models)
        {
            Destroy(model);
        }

        // Step 2: Change the material of the gameobject called 'Plane' to a material loaded from the Furniture folder
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material furnitureMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = furnitureMaterial;

        // Step 3: Substitute the gameobjects 'Desk', 'Table', 'Chair' and 'Chair' with objects loaded from the Furniture folder
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load("Furniture/Table");
        GameObject chair0 = Resources.Load("Furniture/Chair");
        GameObject chair1 = Resources.Load("Furniture/Chair");
        desk.name = "Model_0";
        table.name = "Model_1";
        chair0.name = "Model_2";
        chair1.name = "Model_3";
        GameObject[] furnitureObjects = new GameObject[] { desk, table, chair0, chair1 };
        foreach (GameObject furnitureObject in furnitureObjects)
        {
            furnitureObject.transform.parent = plane.transform;
        }

        // Step 4: Add simple colliders for every object
        foreach (GameObject obj in furnitureObjects)
        {
            BoxCollider boxCollider = obj.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            Rigidbody rb = obj.GetComponent<Rigidbody>();
            if (rb == null)
            {
                rb = obj.AddComponent<Rigidbody>();
            }
        }
    }
}
Elapsed time for the generation of the script took 18,59454 seconds

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using UnityEngine;

public class NaturalTree : MonoBehaviour
{
    // Declare variables for the objects and materials
    public GameObject plane;
    public Material natureMaterial;
    public GameObject[] models;
    public float[] positions;
    public float[] scales;

    void Start()
    {
        // Find the gameobject called 'Plane' and change its material
        plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        natureMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = natureMaterial;

        // Find the gameobjects that are called 'Model_0', 'Model_1', 'Model_2', 'Model_3', and 'Model_4' and destroy them
        models = GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithName("Model_");
        for (int i = 0; i < models.Length; i++)
        {
            Destroy(models[i]);
        }

        // Instantiate the new objects from the Resources/Nature folder
        Vector3 position;
        Quaternion rotation = Quaternion.identity;
        for (int i = 0; i < models.Length; i++)
        {
            string objectName = "Oak";
            if (i == 1 || i == 2)
            {
                objectName = "Pine";
            }
            GameObject newModel = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/" + objectName), Vector3.zero, Quaternion.identity);
            position = positions[i];
            newModel.transform.position = position;
            newModel.transform.rotation = rotation;
            newModel.name = "Model_" + i;
        }

        // Add a box collider for every object
        for (int i = 0; i < models.Length; i++)
        {
            BoxCollider collider = models[i].AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        }
    }
}
Elapsed time for the generation of the script took 12,83503 seconds

using UnityEngine;
using System.Collections.Generic;

public class ObjectInitializer : MonoBehaviour
{
    // Step 1: Destroy specified objects
    void DestroyModels()
    {
        GameObject model_0 = GameObject.Find("Model_0");
        if (model_0 != null) Destroy(model_0);
        
        GameObject model_1 = GameObject.Find("Model_1");
        if (model_1 != null) Destroy(model_1);
        
        GameObject model_2 = GameObject.Find("Model_2");
        if (model_2 != null) Destroy(model_2);
        
        GameObject model_3 = GameObject.Find("Model_3");
        if (model_3 != null) Destroy(model_3);
        
        GameObject model_4 = GameObject.Find("Model_4");
        if (model_4 != null) Destroy(model_4);
    }

    // Step 2: Find the plane and change its material
    void ChangePlaneMaterial()
    {
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
            if (renderer != null && newMaterial != null)
            {
                renderer.material = newMaterial;
            }
        }
    }

    // Step 3: Replace objects and set their positions
    void PlaceObjects()
    {
        GameObject deskObj = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        InstantiateAndPosition(deskObj, "Model_0", 0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f);

        GameObject chairObj1 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        InstantiateAndPosition(chairObj1, "Model_1", 0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f);

        GameObject chairObj2 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");

        GameObject chairObj3 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        InstantiateAndPosition(chairObj3, "Model_4", -4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f);
    }

using System.Collections.Generic;

public class ObjectInitializer : MonoBehaviour
{
    // Step 1: Destroy specified objects
    void DestroyModels()
    {
        GameObject model_0 = GameObject.Find("Model_0");
        if (model_0 != null) Destroy(model_0);
        
        GameObject model_1 = GameObject.Find("Model_1");
        if (model_1 != null) Destroy(model_1);
        
        GameObject model_2 = GameObject.Find("Model_2");
        if (model_2 != null) Destroy(model_2);
        
        GameObject model_3 = GameObject.Find("Model_3");
        if (model_3 != null) Destroy(model_3);
        
        GameObject model_4 = GameObject.Find("Model_4");
        if (model_4 != null) Destroy(model_4);
    }

    // Step 2: Find the plane and change its material
    void ChangePlaneMaterial()
    {
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
            if (renderer != null && newMaterial != null)
            {
                renderer.material = newMaterial;
            }
        }
    }

    // Step 3: Replace objects and set their positions
    void PlaceObjects()
    {
        GameObject deskObj = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        InstantiateAndPosition(deskObj, "Model_0", 0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f);

        GameObject chairObj1 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        InstantiateAndPosition(chairObj1, "Model_1", 0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f);

        GameObject tableObj = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        InstantiateAndPosition(tableObj, "Model_2", -2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f);

        GameObject chairObj2 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        InstantiateAndPosition(chairObj2, "Model_3", -2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f);

        GameObject chairObj3 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        InstantiateAndPosition(chairObj3, "Model_4", -4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f);
    }

    void InstantiateAndPosition(GameObject objToInstantiate, string name, float x, float y, float z)
    {
        GameObject newObject = Instantiate(objToInstantiate);
        newObject.name = name;
        newObject.transform.position = new Vector3(x, y, z);

        // Optional: Rotate if necessary
        if (name == "Model_4")
        {
            newObject.transform.rotation 
Elapsed time for the generation of the script took 36,60144 seconds

 using UnityEngine;

public class FurniturePlacement : MonoBehaviour
{
    public void Start()
    {
        // 1) Find and destroy existing objects
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_0"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_1"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_2"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_3"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_4"));

        // 2) Change plane material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");

        // 3) Load and place new objects
        GameObject model0 = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk"), new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f), Quaternion.identity);
        model0.name = "Model_0";

        GameObject model1 = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"), new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f), Quaternion.identity);
        model1.name = "Model_1";

        GameObject model2 = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table"), new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f), Quaternion.identity);
        model2.name = "Model_2";

        GameObject model3 = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"), new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f), Quaternion.identity);
        model3.name = "Model_3";

        GameObject model4 = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"), new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0));
        model4.name = "Model_4";

        // 4) Add colliders
        foreach (GameObject model in GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithTag("Furniture"))
        {
            model.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        }
    }
}

Model - qwen2.5-coder

You wrote the following  sentence : office​
2024-11-13 16:55:46

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using UnityEngine;

public class InitializeScene : MonoBehaviour
{
    // Step 1: Destroy objects named 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
    private void DestroyModels()
    {
        for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++)
        {
            string modelName = "Model_" + i;
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find(modelName);
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }
    }

    // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' object and change its material
    private void ChangePlaneMaterial()
    {
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
            if (renderer != null && newMaterial != null)
            {
                renderer.material = newMaterial;
            }
        }
    }

    // Step 3: Load objects from the Furniture folder and place them at specified positions
    private void PlaceModels()
    {
        GameObject[] modelsToPlace = { "Desk", "Chair", "Table", "Chair", "Chair" };
        Vector3[] modelPositions = {
            new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f),
            new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),
            new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f),
            new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
            new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f)
        };

        for (int i = 0; i < modelsToPlace.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject modelPrefab = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/" + modelsToPlace[i]);
            if (modelPrefab != null)
            {
                GameObject modelInstance = Instantiate(modelPrefab, modelPositions[i], Quaternion.identity);
                modelInstance.name = "Model_" + i;

                // Step 4: Add a collider to the object
                BoxCollider collider = modelInstance.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
                if (i == 3) // Only rotate the third model (Model_3)
                {
                    modelInstance.transform.Rotate(0, -97.34f, 0);
                }
            }
        }
    }

    void Start()
    {
        // Follow each step in sequence
        DestroyModels();
        ChangePlaneMaterial();
        PlaceModels();
    }
}
Elapsed time for the generation of the script took 30,94553 seconds

 using UnityEngine;

public class InitializeScene : MonoBehaviour

            GameObject model = GameObject.Find(modelName);
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }
    }

    // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' object and change its material
    private void ChangePlaneMaterial()
    {
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
            if (renderer != null && newMaterial != null)
            {
                renderer.material = newMaterial;
            }
        }
    }

    {

        Vector3[] modelPositions = {
            new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f),

            {
                GameObject modelInstance = Instantiate(modelPrefab, modelPositions[i], Quaternion.identity);
                modelInstance.name = "Model_" + i;

                // Step 4: Add a collider to the object

                if (i == 3) // Only rotate the third model (Model_3)
                {
                    modelInstance.transform.Rotate(0, -97.34f, 0);
                }
            }
        }
    }

    void Start()
    {
        // Follow each step in sequence
        DestroyModels();
        ChangePlaneMaterial();
        PlaceModels();
    }

        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
            if (renderer != null && newMaterial != null)
            {
                renderer.material = newMaterial;
            }
        }
    }

    // Step 3: Load objects from the Furniture folder and place them at specified positions
    private void PlaceModels()
    {
        GameObject[] modelsToPlace = { "Desk", "Chair", "Table", "Chair", "Chair" };
        Vector3[] modelPositions = {
            new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f),
            new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),
            new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f),
            new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
            new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f)
        };

        for (int i = 0; i < modelsToPlace.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject modelPrefab = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/" + modelsToPlace[i]);
            if (modelPrefab != null)
            {
                GameObject modelInstance = Instantiate(modelPrefab, modelPositions[i], Quaternion.identity);
                modelInstance.name = "Model_" + i;

                // Step 4: Add a collider to the object
                BoxCollider collider = modelInstance.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
                if (i == 3) // Only rotate the third model (Model_3)
                {
                    modelInstance.transform.Rotate(0, -97.34f, 0);
                }
            }
        }
    }

    void Start()
    {
        // Follow each step in sequence
        DestroyModels();
        ChangePlaneMaterial();
        PlaceModels();
    }
}

public class InitializeScene : MonoBehaviour

Model - qwen2.5-coder

You wrote the following  sentence : office​
2024-11-13 16:56:30

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using the Start() method as requested:


using UnityEngine;

public class SetupScene : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Destroy existing models
        DestroyOldModels();

        // Step 2: Change Plane material
        ChangePlaneMaterial();

        // Step 3: Instantiate new models and position them
        CreateAndPositionModels();
        
        // Step 4: Add colliders to all objects
        AddCollidersToAllObjects();
    }

    private void DestroyOldModels()
    {
        foreach (string modelName in new string[] { "Model_0", "Model_1", "Model_2", "Model_3", "Model_4" })
        {
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find(modelName);
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }
    }

    private void ChangePlaneMaterial()
    {
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        if (newMaterial != null)
        {
            GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
            if (plane != null)
            {
                Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
                if (renderer != null)
                {
                    renderer.material = newMaterial;
                }
            }
        }
    }

    private void CreateAndPositionModels()
    {
        // Load models
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        GameObject chair1 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        GameObject chair2 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");

        if (desk != null && table != null && chair1 != null && chair2 != null)
        {
            // Create and position models
            CreateModel(desk, "Desk", new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f));
            CreateModel(table, "Table", new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f));
            CreateModel(chair1, "Chair_0", new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f));
            CreateModel(chair2, "Chair_1", new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f));
            CreateModel(chair2, "Chair_2", new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f));
        }
    }

    private void CreateModel(GameObject prefab, string name, Vector3 position, Quaternion rotation = default)
    {
        GameObject model = Instantiate(prefab, position, rotation);
        model.name = name;
    }

    private void AddCollidersToAllObjects()
    {
        foreach (GameObject obj in Resources.LoadAll<GameObject>("Furniture"))
        {
            if (!obj.GetComponent<Collider>())
            {
                obj.AddComponent<MeshCollider>();
            }
        }
    }
}
Elapsed time for the generation of the script took 43,18985 seconds

        GameObject chair2 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");

        if (desk != null && table != null && chair1 != null && chair2 != null)
        {
            // Create and position models
            CreateModel(desk, "Desk", new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f));
            CreateModel(table, "Table", new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f));
            CreateModel(chair1, "Chair_0", new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f));
            CreateModel(chair2, "Chair_1", new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f));
            CreateModel(chair2, "Chair_2", new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f));
        }
    }

    private void CreateModel(GameObject prefab, string name, Vector3 position, Quaternion rotation = default)
    {
        GameObject model = Instantiate(prefab, position, rotation);
        model.name = name;
    }

    private void AddCollidersToAllObjects()
    {
        foreach (GameObject obj in Resources.LoadAll<GameObject>("Furniture"))
        {
            if (!obj.GetComponent<Collider>())
            {
                obj.AddComponent<MeshCollider>();
            }

using UnityEngine;

public class SetupScene : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Destroy existing models
        DestroyOldModels();

        // Step 2: Change Plane material
        ChangePlaneMaterial();

        // Step 3: Instantiate new models and position them
        CreateAndPositionModels();
        
        // Step 4: Add colliders to all objects
        AddCollidersToAllObjects();
    }

    private void DestroyOldModels()
    {
        foreach (string modelName in new string[] { "Model_0", "Model_1", "Model_2", "Model_3", "Model_4" })
        {
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find(modelName);
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }
    }

    private void ChangePlaneMaterial()
    {
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        if (newMaterial != null)
        {
            GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
            if (plane != null)
            {
                Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
                if (renderer != null)
                {
                    renderer.material = newMaterial;
                }
            }
        }
    }

    private void CreateAndPositionModels()
    {
        // Load models
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        GameObject chair1 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        GameObject chair2 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");

        if (desk != null && table != null && chair1 != null && chair2 != null)
        {
            // Create and position models
            CreateModel(desk, "Desk", new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f));
            CreateModel(table, "Table", new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f));
            CreateModel(chair1, "Chair_0", new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f));
            CreateModel(chair2, "Chair_1", new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f));
            CreateModel(chair2, "Chair_2", new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f));
        }
    }

    private void CreateModel(GameObject prefab, string name, Vector3 position, Quaternion rotation = default)

        {
            GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
            if (plane != null)
            {
                Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
                if (renderer != null)
                {
                    renderer.material = newMaterial;
                }
            }
        }
    }

    private void CreateAndPositionModels()
    {
        // Load models
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        GameObject chair1 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        GameObject chair2 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");

        if (desk != null && table != null && chair1 != null && chair2 != null)
        {
            // Create and position models
            CreateModel(desk, "Desk", new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f));
            CreateModel(table, "Table", new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f));
            CreateModel(chair1, "Chair_0", new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f));
            CreateModel(chair2, "Chair_1", new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f));
            CreateModel(chair2, "Chair_2", new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f));
        }
    }

    private void CreateModel(GameObject prefab, string name, Vector3 position, Quaternion rotation = default)
    {
        GameObject model = Instantiate(prefab, position, rotation);
        model.name = name;
    }

    private void AddCollidersToAllObjects()
    {
        foreach (GameObject obj in Resources.LoadAll<GameObject>("Furniture"))
        {
            if (!obj.GetComponent<Collider>())
            {
                obj.AddComponent<MeshCollider>();
            }
        }
    }

        AddCollidersToAllObjects();
    }

    private void DestroyOldModels()
    {
        foreach (string modelName in new string[] { "Model_0", "Model_1", "Model_2", "Model_3", "Model_4" })
        {
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find(modelName);
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }
    }

    private void ChangePlaneMaterial()
    {
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        if (newMaterial != null)
        {
            GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
            if (plane != null)
            {
                Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
                if (renderer != null)
                {
                    renderer.material = newMaterial;
                }
            }
        }
    }

    private void CreateAndPositionModels()
    {
        // Load models
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        GameObject chair1 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        GameObject chair2 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");

        if (desk != null && table != null && chair1 != null && chair2 != null)
        {
            // Create and position models
            CreateModel(desk, "Desk", new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f));
            CreateModel(table, "Table", new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f));
            CreateModel(chair1, "Chair_0", new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f));
            CreateModel(chair2, "Chair_1", new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f));
            CreateModel(chair2, "Chair_2", new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f));
        }
    }

    private void CreateModel(GameObject prefab, string name, Vector3 position, Quaternion rotation = default)
    {
        GameObject model = Instantiate(prefab, position, rotation);
        model.name = name;
    }

    private void AddCollidersToAllObjects()
    {
        foreach (GameObject obj in Resources.LoadAll<GameObject>("Furniture"))
        {
            if (!obj.GetComponent<Collider>())
            {
                obj.AddComponent<MeshCollider>();
            }
        }
    }
}

You wrote the following  sentence : office​
2024-11-13 16:56:31

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using the Start() method as requested:


using UnityEngine;

public class SetupScene : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Destroy existing models
        DestroyOldModels();

        // Step 2: Change Plane material
        ChangePlaneMaterial();

        // Step 3: Instantiate new models and position them
        CreateAndPositionModels();
        
        // Step 4: Add colliders to all objects
        AddCollidersToAllObjects();
    }

    private void DestroyOldModels()
    {
        foreach (string modelName in new string[] { "Model_0", "Model_1", "Model_2", "Model_3", "Model_4" })
        {
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find(modelName);
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }
    }

    private void ChangePlaneMaterial()
    {
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        if (newMaterial != null)
        {
            GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
            if (plane != null)
            {
                Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
                if (renderer != null)
                {
                    renderer.material = newMaterial;
                }
            }
        }
    }

    private void CreateAndPositionModels()
    {
        // Load models
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        GameObject chair1 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        GameObject chair2 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");

        if (desk != null && table != null && chair1 != null && chair2 != null)
        {
            // Create and position models
            CreateModel(desk, "Desk", new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f));
            CreateModel(table, "Table", new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f));
            CreateModel(chair1, "Chair_0", new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f));
            CreateModel(chair2, "Chair_1", new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f));
            CreateModel(chair2, "Chair_2", new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f));
        }
    }

    private void CreateModel(GameObject prefab, string name, Vector3 position, Quaternion rotation = default)
    {
        GameObject model = Instantiate(prefab, position, rotation);
        model.name = name;
    }

    private void AddCollidersToAllObjects()
    {
        foreach (GameObject obj in Resources.LoadAll<GameObject>("Furniture"))
        {
            if (!obj.GetComponent<Collider>())
            {
                obj.AddComponent<MeshCollider>();
            }
        }
    }
}
Elapsed time for the generation of the script took 43,18985 seconds

using UnityEngine;

public class SetupScene : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Destroy existing models
        DestroyOldModels();

        // Step 2: Change Plane material
        ChangePlaneMaterial();

        // Step 3: Instantiate new models and position them
        CreateAndPositionModels();
        
        // Step 4: Add colliders to all objects
        AddCollidersToAllObjects();
    }

    private void DestroyOldModels()
    {
        foreach (string modelName in new string[] { "Model_0", "Model_1", "Model_2", "Model_3", "Model_4" })
        {
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find(modelName);
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }
    }

    private void ChangePlaneMaterial()
    {
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        if (newMaterial != null)
        {
            GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
            if (plane != null)
            {
                Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
                if (renderer != null)
                {
                    renderer.material = newMaterial;
                }
            }
        }
    }

    private void CreateAndPositionModels()
    {
        // Load models
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        GameObject chair1 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        GameObject chair2 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");

        if (desk != null && table != null && chair1 != null && chair2 != null)
        {
            // Create and position models
            CreateModel(desk, "Desk", new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f));
            CreateModel(table, "Table", new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f));
            CreateModel(chair1, "Chair_0", new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f));
            CreateModel(chair2, "Chair_1", new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f));
            CreateModel(chair2, "Chair_2", new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f));
        }
    }

    private void CreateModel(GameObject prefab, string name, Vector3 position, Quaternion rotation = default)
    {
        GameObject model = Instantiate(prefab, position, rotation);
        model.name = name;
    }

    private void AddCollidersToAllObjects()
    {
        foreach (GameObject obj in Resources.LoadAll<GameObject>("Furniture"))
        {
            if (!obj.GetComponent<Collider>())
            {
                obj.AddComponent<MeshCollider>();
            }
        }
    }
}

            if (plane != null)

        }
    }

    {

            if (plane != null)

            CreateModel(chair1, "Chair_0", new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f));
            CreateModel(chair2, "Chair_1", new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f));
            CreateModel(chair2, "Chair_2", new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f));
        }
    }

    private void CreateModel(GameObject prefab, string name, Vector3 position, Quaternion rotation = default)
    {
        GameObject model = Instantiate(prefab, position, rotation);
        model.name = name;
    }

    private void AddCollidersToAllObjects()
    {
        foreach (GameObject obj in Resources.LoadAll<GameObject>("Furniture"))
        {
            if (!obj.GetComponent<Collider>())
            {
                obj.AddComponent<MeshCollider>();
            }
        }
    }
}

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using the Start() method as requested:


using UnityEngine;

public class SetupScene : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Destroy existing models
        DestroyOldModels();

        // Step 2: Change Plane material
        ChangePlaneMaterial();

        // Step 3: Instantiate new models and position them
        CreateAndPositionModels();
        
        // Step 4: Add colliders to all objects
        AddCollidersToAllObjects();
    }

    private void DestroyOldModels()
    {
        foreach (string modelName in new string[] { "Model_0", "Model_1", "Model_2", "Model_3", "Model_4" })
        {
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find(modelName);
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }
    }

    private void ChangePlaneMaterial()
    {
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        if (newMaterial != null)
        {
            GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
            if (plane != null)
            {
                Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
                if (renderer != null)
                {
                    renderer.material = newMaterial;
                }
            }
        }
    }

    private void CreateAndPositionModels()
    {
        // Load models
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        GameObject chair1 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        GameObject chair2 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");

        if (desk != null && table != null && chair1 != null && chair2 != null)
        {
            // Create and position models
            CreateModel(desk, "Desk", new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f));
            CreateModel(table, "Table", new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f));
            CreateModel(chair1, "Chair_0", new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f));
            CreateModel(chair2, "Chair_1", new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f));
            CreateModel(chair2, "Chair_2", new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f));
        }
    }

    private void CreateModel(GameObject prefab, string name, Vector3 position, Quaternion rotation = default)
    {
        GameObject model = Instantiate(prefab, position, rotation);
        model.name = name;
    }

    private void AddCollidersToAllObjects()
    {
        foreach (GameObject obj in Resources.LoadAll<GameObject>("Furniture"))
        {
            if (!obj.GetComponent<Collider>())
            {
                obj.AddComponent<MeshCollider>();
            }
        }
    }
}

 using UnityEngine;
using System.Collections;

public class MyScene : MonoBehaviour {
    public GameObject Model_0; // These variables need to be set up in the Inspector for them to work.
    public GameObject Model_1;
    public GameObject Model_2;
    public GameObject Model_3;
    public GameObject Model_4;

    void Start() 
    {  
        Destroy(Model_0);
        Destroy(Model_1);
        Destroy(Model_2);
        Destroy(Model_3);
        Destroy(Model_4);

        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material") as Material; // Loading the material from resources.
        GameObject planeObject = GameObject.Find("Plane"); // Finding the Plane object.
        Renderer renderer = planeObject.GetComponent<Renderer>(); 
        renderer.material = newMaterial;  // Changing the material of the Plane.

        Model_0 = (GameObject)Instantiate(Resources.Load("Furniture/Desk"), new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f), Quaternion.identity);  
        Model_0.name = "Model_0";
        BoxCollider collider = Model_0.AddComponent<BoxCollider>(); // Adding a Collider to Model_0.

        Model_1 = (GameObject)Instantiate(Resources.Load("Furniture/Chair"), new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f), Quaternion.identity);  
        Model_1.name = "Model_1";
        collider = Model_1.AddComponent<BoxCollider>(); // Adding a Collider to Model_1.

        Model_2 = (GameObject)Instantiate(Resources.Load("Furniture/Table"), new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f), Quaternion.identity);  
        Model_2.name = "Model_2";
        collider = Model_2.AddComponent<BoxCollider>(); // Adding a Collider to Model_2.

        Model_3 = (GameObject)Instantiate(Resources.Load("Furniture/Chair"), new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f), Quaternion.identity);  
        Model_3.name = "Model_3";
        collider = Model_3.AddComponent<BoxCollider>(); // Adding a Collider to Model_3.

        Model_4 = (GameObject)Instantiate(Resources.Load("Furniture/Chair"), new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34, 0));  
        Model_4.name = "Model_4";
        collider = Model_4.AddComponent<BoxCollider>(); // Adding a Collider to Model_4.
    }
}

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using only the Start() method:


using UnityEngine;

public class ObjectSetup : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Find and destroy 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_0"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_1"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_2"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_3"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_4"));

        // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' object and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        if (plane != null && newMaterial != null)
        {
            Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
            if (renderer != null)
            {
                renderer.material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and position objects from the Furniture folder
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        GameObject chair1 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        GameObject chair2 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");

        if (desk != null && table != null && chair1 != null && chair2 != null)
        {
            Instantiate(desk, new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f), Quaternion.identity).name = "Model_0";
            Instantiate(chair1, new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f), Quaternion.identity).name = "Model_1";
            Instantiate(table, new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f), Quaternion.identity).name = "Model_2";
            Instantiate(chair2, new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f), Quaternion.identity).name = "Model_3";
            Instantiate(chair2, new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0)).name = "Model_4";
        }

        // Step 4: Add a simple collider to every object
        foreach (GameObject model in GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithTag("Model"))
        {
            if (model.GetComponent<Collider>() == null)
            {
                model.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            }
        }
    }
}
Elapsed time for the generation of the script took 29,74934 seconds

        // Step 1: Find and destroy 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_0"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_1"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_2"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_3"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_4"));

        // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' object and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        if (plane != null && newMaterial != null)
        {
            Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
            if (renderer != null)
            {
                renderer.material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and position objects from the Furniture folder
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        GameObject chair1 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        GameObject chair2 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");

        if (desk != null && table != null && chair1 != null && chair2 != null)
        {
            Instantiate(desk, new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f), Quaternion.identity).name = "Model_0";
            Instantiate(chair1, new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f), Quaternion.identity).name = "Model_1";
            Instantiate(table, new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f), Quaternion.identity).name = "Model_2";
            Instantiate(chair2, new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f), Quaternion.identity).name = "Model_3";
            Instantiate(chair2, new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0)).name = "Model_4";
        }

        // Step 4: Add a simple collider to every object
        foreach (GameObject model in GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithTag("Model"))
        {
            if (model.GetComponent<Collider>() == null)
            {
                model.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            }
        }
    }
}

        {

        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_0"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_1"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_2"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_3"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_4"));

        // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' object and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        if (plane != null && newMaterial != null)
        {
            Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
            if (renderer != null)
            {
                renderer.material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and position objects from the Furniture folder
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        GameObject chair1 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        GameObject chair2 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");

        if (desk != null && table != null && chair1 != null && chair2 != null)
        {
            Instantiate(desk, new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f), Quaternion.identity).name = "Model_0";
            Instantiate(chair1, new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f), Quaternion.identity).name = "Model_1";
            Instantiate(table, new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f), Quaternion.identity).name = "Model_2";
            Instantiate(chair2, new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f), Quaternion.identity).name = "Model_3";
            Instantiate(chair2, new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0)).name = "Model_4";
        }

        // Step 4: Add a simple collider to every object
        foreach (GameObject model in GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithTag("Model"))
        {
            if (model.GetComponent<Collider>() == null)
            {
                model.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            }
        }
    }
}

    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Find and destroy 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_0"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_1"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_2"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_3"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_4"));

        // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' object and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        if (plane != null && newMaterial != null)
        {
            Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
            if (renderer != null)
            {
                renderer.material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and position the objects from 'Furniture' folder
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        List<GameObject> chairs = new List<GameObject>();
        for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) // Assuming there are 2 chairs
        {
            chairs.Add(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"));
        }

        if (desk != null && table != null && chairs.Count > 1)
        {
            GameObject model_0 = Instantiate(desk);
            model_0.name = "Model_0";
            model_0.transform.position = new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f);

            GameObject model_1 = Instantiate(chairs[0]);
            model_1.name = "Model_1";
            model_1.transform.position = new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f);

            GameObject model_2 = Instantiate(table);
            model_2.name = "Model_2";
            model_2.transform.position = new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f);

            GameObject model_3 = Instantiate(chairs[1]);
            model_3.name = "Model_3";
            model_3.transform.position = new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f);

            GameObject model_4 = Instantiate(chairs[1]);
            model_4.name = "Model_4";
            model_4.transform.position = new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f);
            model_4.transform.rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0); // Step 3b rotation
        }

        // Step 4: Add simple colliders to all objects (excluding the plane)
        foreach (GameObject go in GameObject.FindObjectsOfType<GameObject>())
        {
            if (!go.name.Equals("Plane"))
            {
                BoxCollider collider = go.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            }
        }
    }
}

using UnityEngine;
using System.Collections.Generic;

public class SceneSetup : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Find and destroy 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_0"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_1"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_2"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_3"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_4"));

        // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' object and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        if (plane != null && newMaterial != null)
        {
            Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
            if (renderer != null)
            {
                renderer.material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and position the objects from 'Furniture' folder
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        List<GameObject> chairs = new List<GameObject>();
        for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) // Assuming there are 2 chairs
        {
            chairs.Add(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"));
        }

        if (desk != null && table != null && chairs.Count > 1)
        {
            GameObject model_0 = Instantiate(desk);
            model_0.name = "Model_0";
            model_0.transform.position = new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f);

            GameObject model_1 = Instantiate(chairs[0]);
            model_1.name = "Model_1";
            model_1.transform.position = new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f);

            GameObject model_2 = Instantiate(table);
            model_2.name = "Model_2";
            model_2.transform.position = new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f);

            GameObject model_3 = Instantiate(chairs[1]);
            model_3.name = "Model_3";
            model_3.transform.position = new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f);

            GameObject model_4 = Instantiate(chairs[1]);
            model_4.name = "Model_4";
            model_4.transform.position = new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f);
            model_4.transform.rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0); // Step 3b rotation
        }

        // Step 4: Add simple colliders to all objects (excluding the plane)
        foreach (GameObject go in GameObject.FindObjectsOfType<GameObject>())
        {
            if (!go.name.Equals("Plane"))
            {
                BoxCollider collider = go.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            }
        }
    }
}

        if (plane != null && newMaterial != null)
        {
            Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
            if (renderer != null)
            {
                renderer.material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        List<GameObject> chairs = new List<GameObject>();
        for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) // Assuming there are 2 chairs
        {
            chairs.Add(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"));

        if (desk != null && table != null && chairs.Count > 1)

        // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' object and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        if (plane != null && newMaterial != null)
        {
            Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
            if (renderer != null)
            {
                renderer.material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");

        for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) // Assuming there are 2 chairs

            if (renderer != null)
            {
                renderer.material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and position the objects from 'Furniture' folder
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        List<GameObject> chairs = new List<GameObject>();
        for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) // Assuming there are 2 chairs
        {
            chairs.Add(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"));
        }

        if (desk != null && table != null && chairs.Count > 1)
        {
            GameObject model_0 = Instantiate(desk);
            model_0.name = "Model_0";
            model_0.transform.position = new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f);

            GameObject model_1 = Instantiate(chairs[0]);
            model_1.name = "Model_1";
            model_1.transform.position = new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f);

            GameObject model_2 = Instantiate(table);
            model_2.name = "Model_2";
            model_2.transform.position = new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f);

            GameObject model_3 = Instantiate(chairs[1]);
            model_3.name = "Model_3";
            model_3.transform.position = new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f);

            GameObject model_4 = Instantiate(chairs[1]);
            model_4.name = "Model_4";
            model_4.transform.position = new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f);
            model_4.transform.rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0); // Step 3b rotation
        }

        // Step 4: Add simple colliders to all objects (excluding the plane)
        foreach (GameObject go in GameObject.FindObjectsOfType<GameObject>())
        {
            if (!go.name.Equals("Plane"))
            {
                BoxCollider collider = go.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            }
        }
    }
}

        // Step 1: Find and destroy 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_0"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_1"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_2"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_3"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_4"));

        // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' object and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        if (plane != null && newMaterial != null)
        {
            Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
            if (renderer != null)
            {
                renderer.material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and position the objects from 'Furniture' folder
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        List<GameObject> chairs = new List<GameObject>();
        for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) // Assuming there are 2 chairs
        {
            chairs.Add(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"));
        }

        if (desk != null && table != null && chairs.Count > 1)
        {
            GameObject model_0 = Instantiate(desk);
            model_0.name = "Model_0";
            model_0.transform.position = new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f);

            GameObject model_1 = Instantiate(chairs[0]);
            model_1.name = "Model_1";
            model_1.transform.position = new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f);

            GameObject model_2 = Instantiate(table);
            model_2.name = "Model_2";
            model_2.transform.position = new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f);

            GameObject model_3 = Instantiate(chairs[1]);
            model_3.name = "Model_3";
            model_3.transform.position = new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f);

            GameObject model_4 = Instantiate(chairs[1]);
            model_4.name = "Model_4";
            model_4.transform.position = new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f);
            model_4.transform.rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0); // Step 3b rotation
        }

        // Step 4: Add simple colliders to all objects (excluding the plane)
        foreach (GameObject go in GameObject.FindObjectsOfType<GameObject>())
        {
            if (!go.name.Equals("Plane"))
            {
                BoxCollider collider = go.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            }
        }
    }
}

using UnityEngine;
using System.Collections.Generic;

public class SceneSetup : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Find and destroy 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_0"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_1"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_2"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_3"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_4"));

        // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' object and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        if (plane != null && newMaterial != null)
        {
            Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
            if (renderer != null)
            {
                renderer.material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and position the objects from 'Furniture' folder
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        List<GameObject> chairs = new List<GameObject>();
        for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) // Assuming there are 2 chairs
        {
            chairs.Add(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"));
        }

        if (desk != null && table != null && chairs.Count > 1)
        {
            GameObject model_0 = Instantiate(desk);
            model_0.name = "Model_0";
            model_0.transform.position = new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f);

            GameObject model_1 = Instantiate(chairs[0]);
            model_1.name = "Model_1";
            model_1.transform.position = new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f);

            GameObject model_2 = Instantiate(table);
            model_2.name = "Model_2";
            model_2.transform.position = new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f);

            GameObject model_3 = Instantiate(chairs[1]);
            model_3.name = "Model_3";
            model_3.transform.position = new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f);

            GameObject model_4 = Instantiate(chairs[1]);
            model_4.name = "Model_4";
            model_4.transform.position = new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f);
            model_4.transform.rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0); // Step 3b rotation
        }

        // Step 4: Add simple colliders to all objects (excluding the plane)
        foreach (GameObject go in GameObject.FindObjectsOfType<GameObject>())
        {
            if (!go.name.Equals("Plane"))
            {
                BoxCollider collider = go.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            }
        }
    }
}

            model_4.name = "Model_4";

            model_4.transform.rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0); // Step 3b rotation
        }

        foreach (GameObject go in GameObject.FindObjectsOfType<GameObject>())
        {
            if (!go.name.Equals("Plane"))
            {
                BoxCollider collider = go.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            }
        }
    }

using UnityEngine;
using System.Collections.Generic;

public class SceneSetup : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Find and destroy 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_0"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_1"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_2"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_3"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_4"));

        // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' object and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        if (plane != null && newMaterial != null)
        {
            Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
            if (renderer != null)
            {
                renderer.material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and position the objects from 'Furniture' folder
        GameObject desk = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        List<GameObject> chairs = new List<GameObject>();
        for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) // Assuming there are 2 chairs
        {
            chairs.Add(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"));
        }

        if (desk != null && table != null && chairs.Count > 1)
        {
            GameObject model_0 = Instantiate(desk);
            model_0.name = "Model_0";

 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureLoader : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Find and destroy objects named 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        for (int i = 0; i <= 4; i++)
        {
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find("Model_" + i);
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }

        // Step 2: Find the Plane and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            if (newMaterial != null)
            {
                plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and place furniture objects
        GameObject[] furnitureNames = { "Desk", "Chair", "Table", "Chair", "Chair" };
        Vector3[] positions = 
        {
            new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f),
            new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),
            new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f),
            new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
            new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f)
        };
        Quaternion[] rotations = { Quaternion.identity, Quaternion.identity, Quaternion.identity,
                                  Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0), Quaternion.identity };

        for (int i = 0; i < furnitureNames.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject furniturePrefab = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/" + furnitureNames[i]);
            if (furniturePrefab != null)
            {
                GameObject newObject = Instantiate(furniturePrefab);
                newObject.name = "Model_" + i;
                newObject.transform.position = positions[i];
                newObject.transform.rotation = rotations[i];

                // Step 4: Add a simple collider to the object
                BoxCollider boxCollider = newObject.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
                if (boxCollider != null)
                {
                    boxCollider.center = Vector3.zero;
                    boxCollider.size = new Vector3(1, 1, 1);
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureManager : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Destroy existing objects
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_0"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_1"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_2"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_3"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_4"));

        // Step 2: Change the material of 'Plane'
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            if (newMaterial != null)
            {
                plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
            }
            else
            {
                Debug.LogError("Material not found in 'Furniture/Material'");
            }
        }
        else
        {
            Debug.LogError("'Plane' object not found");
        }

        // Step 3: Load and position the new objects
        GameObject[] furnitureObjects = { 
            Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk"), 
            Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"), 
            Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table"), 
            Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"),
            Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair")
        };

        if (furnitureObjects != null)
        {
            Vector3[] positions = { new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f), 
                                    new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),
                                    new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f),
                                    new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
                                    new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f) };

            float rotationY = -97.34f;

            for (int i = 0; i < furnitureObjects.Length; i++)
            {
                if (i == 1) // Rotate the second chair
                {
                    GameObject newChair = Instantiate(furnitureObjects[i], positions[i], Quaternion.Euler(0, rotationY, 0));
                    newChair.name = "Model_3"; // Renaming as Model_3 since we don't have specific names for others
                }
                else if (i == 2) // Rename the table to Model_2
                {
                    GameObject table = Instantiate(furnitureObjects[i], positions[i], Quaternion.identity);
                    table.name = "Model_2";
                }
                else
                {
                    GameObject newObject = Instantiate(furnitureObjects[i], positions[i], Quaternion.identity);
                    newObject.name = $"Model_{i}"; // Renaming accordingly
                }

                // Step 4: Add a simple collider to every object
                if (newObject != null)
                {
                    BoxCollider boxCollider = newObject.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
                    Vector3 size = new ObjectSizeEstimator().GetSize(newObject); // Assuming you have an ObjectSizeEstimator utility class
                    boxCollider.size = size;
                }
            }
        }
        else
        {
            Debug.LogError("Furniture objects not found in the 'Furniture' folder");
        }
    }
}

// Utility class to estimate object size (modify as needed)
public class ObjectSizeEstimator
{
    public Vector3 GetSize(GameObject obj)
    {
        Bounds bounds = new Bounds(obj.transform.position, Vector3.zero);
        Renderer[] renderers = obj.GetComponentsInChildren<Renderer>();
        
        foreach (Renderer renderer in renderers)
        {
            bounds.Encapsulate(renderer.bounds);
        }

        return bounds.size;
    }
}

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using UnityEngine;

public class SceneSetup : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Find and destroy objects called 'Model_0', 'Model_1', 'Model_2', 'Model_3', 'Model_4'
        string[] modelsToDestroy = { "Model_0", "Model_1", "Model_2", "Model_3", "Model_4" };
        foreach (string model in modelsToDestroy)
        {
            GameObject obj = GameObject.Find(model);
            if (obj != null)
            {
                Destroy(obj);
            }
        }

        // Step 2: Find the gameobject 'Plane' and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            if (newMaterial != null)
            {
                Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
                if (renderer != null)
                {
                    renderer.material = newMaterial;
                }
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Substitute them with objects loaded from the Furniture folder
        string[] furnitureNames = { "Desk", "Chair", "Table", "Chair", "Chair" };
        Vector3[] positions = 
        {
            new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f),
            new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),
            new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f),
            new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
            new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f)
        };
        Quaternion rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0f, -97.34f, 0f);

        for (int i = 0; i < furnitureNames.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject newFurniture = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/" + furnitureNames[i]);
            if (newFurniture != null)
            {

                collider.size = new Vector3(1f, 1f, 1f); // Adjust size as needed
            }
        }
    }
