 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureManager : MonoBehaviour
{
    private GameObject plane;
    private Material newMaterial;

    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Find and destroy 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        for (int i = 0; i <= 4; i++)
        {
            string modelName = "Model_" + i;
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find(modelName);
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }

        // Step 2: Find and change the material of 'Plane'
        plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            if (newMaterial != null)
            {
                plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
            }
            else
            {
                Debug.LogError("Material not found in Resources/Furniture/Material");
            }
        }
        else
        {
            Debug.LogError("'Plane' not found in the scene.");
        }

        // Step 3: Load and position objects from the Furniture folder
        string[] objectNames = { "Desk", "Chair", "Table", "Chair", "Chair" };
        Vector3[] positions = 
        {
            new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f),
            new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),
            new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f),
            new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
            new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f)
        };
        Quaternion rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0f, -97.34f, 0f);

        for (int i = 0; i < objectNames.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject newObject = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/" + objectNames[i]));
            if (newObject != null)
            {
                newObject.name = "Model_" + i;
                newObject.transform.position = positions[i];
                if (objectNames[i] == "Chair" && i == 4) // Only rotate the last chair
                {
                    newObject.transform.rotation = rotation;
                }
            }
            else
            {
                Debug.LogError("Failed to load object from Resources/Furniture/" + objectNames[i]);
            }
        }

        // Step 4: Add a simple collider for every object
        Collider[] colliders = FindObjectsOfType<Collider>();
        foreach (var collider in colliders)
        {
            if (!collider.gameObject.CompareTag("Ignore")) // Ignore specific objects if needed
            {
                BoxCollider boxCollider = collider as BoxCollider;
                if (boxCollider == null)
                {
                    boxCollider = collider.gameObject.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureLoader : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Destroy objects named 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        for (int i = 0; i <= 4; i++)
        {
            string modelName = $"Model_{i}";
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find(modelName);
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }

        // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' gameobject and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            if (newMaterial != null)
            {
                plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and instantiate objects from the Furniture folder
        string[] furnitureNames = { "Desk", "Chair", "Table", "Chair", "Chair" };
        Vector3[] positions = 
        {
            new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f),
            new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),
            new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f),
            new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
            new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f)
        };
        Quaternion rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0); // For Model_4

        for (int i = 0; i < furnitureNames.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject furnitureObject = Resources.Load<GameObject>($"Furniture/{furnitureNames[i]}");
            if (furnitureObject != null)
            {
                GameObject instantiatedFurniture = Instantiate(furnitureObject);
                instantiatedFurniture.name = $"Model_{i}";

                Vector3 position;
                if (i == 4) // Model_4 has a specific rotation
                {
                    position = positions[4];
                    instantiatedFurniture.transform.rotation = rotation;
                }
                else
                {
                    position = positions[i];
                }

                instantiatedFurniture.transform.position = position;
            }
        }

        // Step 4: Add a simple collider for every object
        Collider[] colliders = FindObjectsOfType<Collider>();
        foreach (Collider collider in colliders)
        {
            BoxCollider boxCollider = collider as BoxCollider;
            if (boxCollider == null)
            {
                boxCollider = gameObject.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            }
        }

        // Optional: Adjust the size of the collider to fit your objects
        foreach (GameObject furnitureObject in GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithTag("Furniture"))
        {
            Collider furnitureCollider = furnitureObject.GetComponent<Collider>();
            if (furnitureCollider != null)
            {
                furnitureCollider.size = new Vector3(1, 1, 1); // Adjust as needed
            }
        }
    }
}

        chair3.name = "Model_4";
        AddCollider(chair3);
    }

    void DestroyGameObject(string name)
    {
        GameObject obj = GameObject.Find(name);
        if (obj != null)
        {
            Destroy(obj);
        }
    }

    void AddCollider(GameObject obj)
    {
        Collider collider = obj.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        // Set the size of the collider based on your needs
        collider.size = new Vector3(1, 1, 1);

 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureLoader : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Destroy existing models
        GameObject[] models = { 
            GameObject.Find("Model_0"),
            GameObject.Find("Model_1"),
            GameObject.Find("Model_2"),
            GameObject.Find("Model_3"),
            GameObject.Find("Model_4")
        };

        foreach (GameObject model in models)
        {
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }

        // Step 2: Change the material of 'Plane'
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            if (newMaterial != null)
            {
                plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and instantiate furniture objects
        GameObject[] furnitureNames = { "Desk", "Chair", "Table", "Chair", "Chair" };
        Vector3[] positions = { 
            new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f), 
            new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f), 
            new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f),
            new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
            new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f)
        };

            Quaternion.identity,

        };

            if (prefab != null)
            {
                GameObject instantiatedObject = Instantiate(prefab, positions[i], rotations[i]);

                if (collider != null)
                {

                }
            }
        }
    }

        {

            if (model != null)

        if (plane != null)

                }
            }

 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureSetup : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Find and destroy objects 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        for (int i = 0; i <= 4; i++)
        {
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find($"Model_{i}");
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }

        // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            if (newMaterial != null)
            {
                plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and instantiate furniture objects
        GameObject[] furniturePrefabs = { Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk"), 
                                         Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"), 
                                         Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table"), 
                                         Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"),
                                         Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair") };

        Vector3[] positions = { new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f),
                                new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),
                                new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f),
                                new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
                                new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f) };

        Quaternion[] rotations = { Quaternion.identity,
                                    Quaternion.identity,
                                    Quaternion.identity,
                                    Quaternion.identity,
                                    Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0) };

        for (int i = 0; i <= 4; i++)
        {
            GameObject furniture = Instantiate(furniturePrefabs[i], positions[i], rotations[i]);
            furniture.name = $"Model_{i}";
        }

        // Step 4: Add a simple collider to every object
        Collider[] colliders = FindObjectsOfType<Collider>();
        foreach (Collider collider in colliders)
        {
            if (!collider.gameObject.CompareTag("Terrain") && !collider.gameObject.CompareTag("Ignore"))
            {
                BoxCollider boxCollider = collider as BoxCollider;
                if (boxCollider == null)
                {
                    boxCollider = collider.gameObject.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
                }
                boxCollider.size = new Vector3(1, 1, 1);
            }
        }
    }
}

 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureManager : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Destroy objects with names 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        string[] modelNames = { "Model_0", "Model_1", "Model_2", "Model_3", "Model_4" };
        foreach (string modelName in modelNames)
        {
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find(modelName);
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }

        // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' gameobject and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            if (newMaterial != null)
            {
                plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and instantiate furniture objects
        string[] furnitureNames = { "Desk", "Chair", "Table", "Chair", "Chair" };
        Vector3[] positions = 
        {
            new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f),
            new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),
            new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f),
            new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
            new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f)
        };
        Quaternion rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0);

        for (int i = 0; i < furnitureNames.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject instantiatedFurniture = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/" + furnitureNames[i]));
            instantiatedFurniture.name = "Model_" + i;
            instantiatedFurniture.transform.position = positions[i];
            if (i == 4) // Only apply rotation to the fifth chair
            {
                instantiatedFurniture.transform.rotation = rotation;
            }
        }

        // Step 4: Add a simple collider for every object
        GameObject[] furnitureObjects = GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithTag("Furniture");
        foreach (GameObject furnitureObject in furnitureObjects)
        {
            BoxCollider boxCollider = furnitureObject.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            boxCollider.size = new Vector3(1f, 1f, 1f); // Adjust size as needed
        }
    }
}

public class FurnitureManager : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()

        // Step 1: Destroy objects with names 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        for (int i = 0; i <= 4; i++)
        {
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find("Model_" + i);
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }

        // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' gameobject and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            if (newMaterial != null)
            {
                plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Instantiate objects from the Furniture folder and position them
        GameObject[] furnitureNames = { "Desk", "Chair", "Table", "Chair", "Chair" };
        Vector3[] positions = {
            new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f),
            new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureSpawner : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Find and destroy 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        string[] modelNames = { "Model_0", "Model_1", "Model_2", "Model_3", "Model_4" };
        foreach (string modelName in modelNames)
        {
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find(modelName);
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }

        // Step 2: Change the material of 'Plane' and rename it
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            if (newMaterial != null)
            {
                plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
            }
            plane.name = "Floor";
        }

        // Step 3: Instantiate furniture objects and rename them
        string[] furnitureNames = { "Desk", "Chair", "Table", "Chair", "Chair" };
        Vector3[] positions = 
        {
            new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f),
            new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),
            new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f),
            new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
            new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f)
        };
        Quaternion[] rotations = 
        {
            Quaternion.identity,
            Quaternion.identity,
            Quaternion.identity,
            Quaternion.identity,
            Quaternion.Euler(0f, -97.34f, 0f) // Only rotate the last chair
        };

        for (int i = 0; i < furnitureNames.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject furniture = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/" + furnitureNames[i]));
            furniture.name = "Model_" + i;
            furniture.transform.position = positions[i];
            if (furnitureNames[i] != "Desk") // Only rotate the last chair
            {
                furniture.transform.rotation = rotations[i];
            }
        }

        // Step 4: Add a simple collider for every object
        foreach (GameObject obj in GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithTag("Furniture"))
        {
            BoxCollider boxCollider = obj.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            if (obj.name == "Model_0") // Desk needs to be wider
            {
                boxCollider.size = new Vector3(1f, 1f, 2.5f);
                boxCollider.center = new Vector3(0f, -0.47f, 0f);
            }
            else if (obj.name == "Model_1" || obj.name == "Model_2") // Table and Chair
            {
                boxCollider.size = new Vector3(1f, 1f, 1f);
                boxCollider.center = new Vector3(0f, -0.47f, 0f);
            }
        }

        // Optional: Add a tag to the furniture objects for easy selection in Unity
        foreach (GameObject obj in GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithTag("Furniture"))
        {
            obj.tag = "Furniture";
        }
    }
}

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using UnityEngine;

public class SceneManagement : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Find and destroy 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++)
        {
            GameObject modelObject = GameObject.Find($"Model_{i}");
            if (modelObject != null)
            {
                Destroy(modelObject);
            }
        }

        // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            if (newMaterial != null)
            {
                plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Instantiate and position the objects from the Furniture folder
        GameObject[] furnitureObjects = { "Desk", "Chair", "Table", "Chair" };
        Vector3[] positions = 
        {
            new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f),
            new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),
            new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f),
            new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
            new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f)
        };
        Quaternion rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0f, -97.34f, 0f);

        for (int i = 0; i < furnitureObjects.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject prefab = Resources.Load<GameObject>($"Furniture/{furnitureObjects[i]}");
            if (prefab != null)
            {
                GameObject instantiatedObject = Instantiate(prefab);
                instantiatedObject.name = $"Model_{i}";
                instantiatedObject.transform.position = positions[i];
                if (i == 0) // Only rotate the first 'Chair' object
                {
                    instantiatedObject.transform.rotation = rotation;
                }
                AddCollider(instantiatedObject); // Step 4: Add a simple collider to every object
            }
        }
    }

    void AddCollider(GameObject obj)
    {
        BoxCollider boxCollider = obj.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        if (boxCollider != null)
        {
            Vector3 size = new Vector3(1f, 1f, 1f); // Adjust the size as needed
            boxCollider.size = size;
        }
    }
}

 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureLoader : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Find and destroy the models
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_0"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_1"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_2"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_3"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_4"));

        // Step 2: Change the material of the Plane
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
            if (renderer != null)
            {
                renderer.material = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and instantiate the new objects
        string[] objectNames = { "Desk", "Chair", "Table", "Chair", "Chair" };
        Vector3[] positions = 
        {
            new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f),
            new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),
            new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f),
            new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
            new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f)
        };
        
        Quaternion rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0f, -97.34f, 0f);

        for (int i = 0; i < objectNames.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject newObj = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/" + objectNames[i]));
            newObj.name = "Model_" + i;
            newObj.transform.position = positions[i];
            if (i == 4) // Rotate the last chair
            {
                newObj.transform.rotation = rotation;
            }
            
            // Step 4: Add a simple collider to each object
            if (!newObj.GetComponent<Collider>())
            {
                Collider collider = newObj.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
                collider.size = new Vector3(1f, 1f, 1f); // Adjust the size as needed
            }
        }
    }
}

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureLoader : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Find and destroy 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++)
        {
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find($"Model_{i}");
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }

        // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            if (newMaterial != null)
            {
                plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and instantiate 'Desk', 'Table', 'Chair' into the scene
        GameObject deskPrefab = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        GameObject tablePrefab = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");
        GameObject chairPrefab1 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        GameObject chairPrefab2 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");

        if (deskPrefab != null && tablePrefab != null && chairPrefab1 != null && chairPrefab2 != null)
        {
            // Instantiate Desk
            GameObject desk = Instantiate(deskPrefab, new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f), Quaternion.identity);
            desk.name = "Model_0";

            foreach (Collider col in colliders)
            {
                BoxCollider boxCollider = col.gameObject.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
                boxCollider.center = Vector3.zero;
                boxCollider.size = new Vector3(1f, 1f, 1f); // Adjust size as needed
            }

 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureSetup : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Destroy objects 'Model_0', 'Model_1', 'Model_2', 'Model_3', 'Model_4'
        GameObject[] modelsToDelete = new GameObject[] { "Model_0", "Model_1", "Model_2", "Model_3", "Model_4" };
        foreach (GameObject model in modelsToDelete)
        {
            GameObject obj = GameObject.Find(model);
            if (obj != null)
            {
                Destroy(obj);
            }
        }

        // Step 2: Change the material of the 'Plane' object
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            if (newMaterial != null)
            {
                plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and place the new objects
        GameObject[] newObjects = new GameObject[]
        {
            Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk"),
            Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"),
            Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table"),
            Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"),
            Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair")
        };

        string[] objectNames = { "Model_0", "Model_1", "Model_2", "Model_3", "Model_4" };
        Vector3[] positions = {
            new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f),
            new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),
            new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f),
            new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
            new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f)
        };
        Quaternion rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0); // Rotation for Model_4

        for (int i = 0; i < newObjects.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject newObj = Instantiate(newObjects[i]);
            newObj.name = objectNames[i];
            newObj.transform.position = positions[i];

            if (i == 4)
            {
                newObj.transform.rotation = rotation;
            }

            // Step 4: Add a simple collider for every object
            Collider collider = newObj.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            if (newObj.CompareTag("Chair") || newObj.CompareTag("Table"))
            {
                collider.size = new Vector3(1, 0.5f, 1); // Adjust the size as needed
            }
        }
    }
}

 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureLoader : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Destroy objects with names 'Model_0', 'Model_1', 'Model_2', 'Model_3', and 'Model_4'
        foreach (string modelName in new string[] { "Model_0", "Model_1", "Model_2", "Model_3", "Model_4" })
        {
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find(modelName);
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }

        // Step 2: Find the 'Plane' and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            if (newMaterial != null)
            {
                plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
            }
            else
            {
                Debug.LogError("Material not found in resources: Furniture/Material");
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and instantiate furniture objects from the 'Furniture' folder
        string[] furnitureNames = { "Desk", "Chair", "Table", "Chair" };
        Vector3[] positions = 
        {
            new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f),
            new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),
            new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f),
            new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
            new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f)
        };
        Quaternion rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0);

        for (int i = 0; i < furnitureNames.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject furniture = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/" + furnitureNames[i]);
            if (furniture != null)
            {
                GameObject instantiatedFurniture = Instantiate(furniture);
                instantiatedFurniture.name = $"Model_{i}";
                instantiatedFurniture.transform.position = positions[i];
                if (i == 0) // Only set rotation for the first 'Chair' (Desk has no rotation)
                {
                    instantiatedFurniture.transform.rotation = rotation;
                }
            }
            else
            {
                Debug.LogError($"Furniture not found in resources: Furniture/{furnitureNames[i]}");
            }

            // Step 4: Add a simple collider to every object
            Collider collider = instantiatedFurniture.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        }
    }
}

 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureManager : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Destroy objects with names 'Model_0', 'Model_1', 'Model_2', 'Model_3', 'Model_4'
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_0"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_1"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_2"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_3"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_4"));

        // Step 2: Change the material of the 'Plane' game object
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            if (newMaterial != null)
            {
                plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
            }
            else
            {
                Debug.LogError("Material not found in 'Furniture' folder.");
            }
        }
        else
        {
            Debug.LogError("'Plane' object not found.");
        }

        // Step 3: Replace destroyed objects with new ones from the Furniture folder
        GameObject[] newModels = { "Desk", "Chair", "Table", "Chair", "Chair" };
        Vector3[] positions = {
            new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f),
            new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),
            new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f),
            new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
            new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f)
        };
        Quaternion rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0);

        for (int i = 0; i < newModels.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject prefab = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/" + newModels[i]);
            if (prefab != null)
            {
                GameObject newObj = Instantiate(prefab);
                newObj.name = "Model_" + i;
                newObj.transform.position = positions[i];
                newObj.transform.rotation = rotation;

                // Step 4: Add a simple collider to every object
                BoxCollider newCollider = newObj.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
                if (newObj.GetComponent<Renderer>() != null)
                {
                    Collider bounds = newObj.GetComponent<Renderer>().bounds;
                    newCollider.center = bounds.extents;
                    newCollider.size = bounds.size;
                }
            }
            else
            {
                Debug.LogError("Prefab not found for: " + newModels[i]);
            }
        }
    }
}

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureManager : MonoBehaviour
{
    private GameObject[] models = new GameObject[5];
    private Material planeMaterial;
    private string[] furnitureNames = { "Desk", "Chair", "Table", "Chair", "Chair" };
    private Vector3[] positions = {
        new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f),
        new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),
        new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f),
        new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
        new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f)
    };
    private Quaternion rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0f, -97.34f, 0f);

    void Start()
    {
        // Destroy existing models
        for (int i = 0; i < models.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find(models[i].name);
            if (model != null)
                Destroy(model);
        }

        // Load plane material
        planeMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");

        // Find and destroy Plane object
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = planeMaterial;
            Destroy(plane);
        }

        // Load new models and set their positions/rotation/collider
        for (int i = 0; i < furnitureNames.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject model = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/" + furnitureNames[i]));
            model.name = "Model_" + i;
            model.transform.position = positions[i];
            if (furnitureNames[i] == "Chair")
                model.transform.rotation = rotation;
            model.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            models[i] = model;
        }
    }
}

            if (model != null)

            }

        // Step 2: Change the material of the 'Plane' object
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {

            if (newMaterial != null)
            {
                Renderer renderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
                if (renderer != null)

                    renderer.material = newMaterial;
                }
            }

using UnityEngine;

public class SceneManagement : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Destroy objects called 'Model_0', 'Model_1', 'Model_2', 'Model_3', 'Model_4'
        GameObject[] modelsToDelete = { 
            GameObject.Find("Model_0"), 
            GameObject.Find("Model_1"), 
            GameObject.Find("Model_2"), 
            GameObject.Find("Model_3"), 
            GameObject.Find("Model_4") 
        };

        foreach (GameObject model in modelsToDelete)
        {
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }

        // Step 2: Change the material of the 'Plane' object
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            if (newMaterial != null)
            {
                plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
            }
            else
            {
                Debug.LogError("Material not found in the 'Furniture' folder.");
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Instantiate and position objects from the Furniture folder
        string[] furnitureNames = { "Desk", "Chair", "Table", "Chair" };
        Vector3[] positions = { 
            new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f), 
            new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f), 
            new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f), 
            new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f) 
        };

            Quaternion.identity, 
            Quaternion.identity, 
            Quaternion.identity, 
            Quaternion.Euler(0f, -97.34f, 0f) 
        };

        for (int i = 0; i < furnitureNames.Length; i++)
        {

            if (furniture != null)

                furniture.transform.rotation = rotations[i];

                // Step 4: Add a simple collider to each object
                BoxCollider boxCollider = furniture.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
                if (boxCollider != null)

                    boxCollider.size = new Vector3(1f, 1f, 1f);
                }
            }
        }

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureLoader : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step 1: Destroy objects with names 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++)
        {
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find("Model_" + i);
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }

        // Step 2: Change the material of the Plane
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Renderer planeRenderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
            if (planeRenderer != null)
            {
                Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
                if (newMaterial != null)
                {
                    planeRenderer.material = newMaterial;
                }
            }
        }

        // Step 3: Load and place the furniture objects
        GameObject[] furniture = { "Desk", "Chair", "Table", "Chair", "Chair" };
        Vector3[] positions = 
        {
            new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f),
            new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),
            new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f),
            new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
            new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f)
        };

        Quaternion rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0);

        for (int i = 0; i < furniture.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject newObject = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/" + furniture[i]), positions[i], i == 4 ? rotation : Quaternion.identity);
            newObject.name = "Model_" + i;
        }

        // Step 4: Add a simple collider for every object
        Collider[] colliders = FindObjectsOfType<Collider>();
        foreach (var collider in colliders)
        {
            if (!collider.gameObject.name.StartsWith("Model_"))
                continue;

            BoxCollider boxCollider = collider as BoxCollider;
            if (boxCollider == null)
            {
                boxCollider = collider.gameObject.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            }
            boxCollider.size = new Vector3(1, 1, 1); // Adjust size as necessary
        }
    }
}

 using UnityEngine;
using System.Collections;

public class Room : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // STEP ONE - Find and destroy objects 'Model_0' to 'Model_4'
        GameObject[] models = new GameObject[]{
            GameObject.Find("Model_0"),
            GameObject.Find("Model_1"),
            GameObject.Find("Model_2"),
            GameObject.Find("Model_3"),
            GameObject.Find("Model_4")
        };
        foreach (GameObject model in models)
        {
            Destroy(model);
        }

        // STEP TWO - Find the 'Plane' gameobject and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");

        // STEP THREE - Load and instantiate objects from the Furniture folder and rename them

            Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk"), new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f), Quaternion.identity),
            Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"), new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0)),
            Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table"), new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f), Quaternion.identity),
            Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"), new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0)),
            Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"), new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0))
        };

        furniture[1].name = "Model_1";
        furniture[2].name = "Model_2";
        furniture[3].name = "Model_3";
        furniture[4].name = "Model_4";

        // STEP FOUR - Add a simple collider to every object
        foreach (GameObject object in furniture)
        {
            object.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        }
    }

The faulty script generated by the AI is the following: 
 using the specified methods. This script should be attached to an appropriate GameObject in your scene, such as an empty GameObject designated for initialization tasks.


using UnityEngine;

public class ObjectManager : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // STEP ONE: Find and destroy Model_0, Model_1, Model_2, Model_3, Model_4
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_0"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_1"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_2"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_3"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_4"));

        // STEP TWO: Find the Plane and change its material
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
            if (newMaterial != null)
            {
                plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
            }
            else
            {
                Debug.LogWarning("Material not found at path: Furniture/Material.");
            }
        }
        else
        {
            Debug.LogWarning("GameObject 'Plane' not found.");
        }

        // STEP THREE: Instantiate new objects from the Furniture folder
        var desk = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk");
        var chair = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair");
        var table = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table");

        if (desk != null) InstantiateWithName(desk, "Model_0", new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0));
        if (chair != null) InstantiateWithName(chair, "Model_1", new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0));
        if (table != null) InstantiateWithName(table, "Model_2", new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0));
        if (chair != null) InstantiateWithName(chair, "Model_3", new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0));
        if (chair != null) InstantiateWithName(chair, "Model_4", new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f), Quaternion.Euler(0, -97.34f, 0));
    }

    // Helper method to instantiate objects with a name and collider
    private void InstantiateWithName(GameObject prefab, string name, Vector3 position, Quaternion rotation)
    {
        GameObject newObject = Instantiate(prefab, position, rotation);
        newObject.name = name;
        newObject.AddComponent<BoxCollider>(); // Adding a simple collider
    }
}

 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureController : MonoBehaviour
{
    public GameObject modelPrefab;
    public Material newMaterial;

    void Start()
    {
        // STEP ONE
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_0"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_1"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_2"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_3"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_4"));

        // STEP TWO
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Renderer planeRenderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
        planeRenderer.material = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");

        // STEP THREE
        InstantiateAndSetModel("Model_0", "Desks/Desk", new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f), Quaternion.identity);
        InstantiateAndSetModel("Model_1", "Chairs/Chair", new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f), Quaternion.identity);
        InstantiateAndSetModel("Model_2", "Tables/Table", new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f), Quaternion.identity);
        InstantiateAndSetModel("Model_3", "Chairs/Chair", new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f), Quaternion.identity);
        GameObject model4 = InstantiateAndSetModel("Model_4", "Chairs/Chair", new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f), Quaternion.Euler(0f, -97.34f, 0f));

        // STEP FOUR
        AddSimpleCollider("Model_0");
        AddSimpleCollider("Model_1");
        AddSimpleCollider("Model_2");
        AddSimpleCollider("Model_3");
        AddSimpleCollider("Model_4");
    }

    private GameObject InstantiateAndSetModel(string modelName, string prefabPath, Vector3 position, Quaternion rotation)
    {
        GameObject model = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/" + prefabPath), position, rotation);
        model.name = modelName;
        return model;
    }

    private void AddSimpleCollider(string modelName)
    {
        GameObject model = GameObject.Find(modelName);
        model.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
    }
}

 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureManager : MonoBehaviour
{
    public GameObject modelPrefab;
    public GameObject planeObject;

    void Start()
    {
        // STEP ONE
        DestroyModels();

        // STEP TWO
        ChangePlaneMaterial();

        // STEP THREE
        LoadAndInstantiateFurniture();

        // STEP FOUR
        AddColliders();
    }

    void DestroyModels()
    {
        for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++)
        {
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find("Model_" + i);
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }
    }

    void ChangePlaneMaterial()
    {
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        planeObject.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
    }

    void LoadAndInstantiateFurniture()
    {
        string[] furnitureNames = { "Desk", "Chair", "Table", "Chair", "Chair" };
        Vector3[] positions = { new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f), new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f),
                                new Vector3(-2.64f, -0.47f, 4.62f), new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f),
                                new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f) };

        for (int i = 0; i < furnitureNames.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject furniture = Instantiate(modelPrefab, positions[i], Quaternion.identity);
            furniture.name = "Model_" + i;
            furniture.transform.rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0f, -97.34f, 0f);
        }
    }

    void AddColliders()
    {
        GameObject[] models = GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithTag("Model");

        foreach (GameObject model in models)
        {
            model.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        }
    }
}

 using UnityEngine;

public class FurnitureController : MonoBehaviour
{
    // Step One
    private void DestroyOldModels()
    {
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_0"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_1"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_2"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_3"));
        Destroy(GameObject.Find("Model_4"));
    }

    // Step Two
    private void ChangePlaneMaterial()
    {
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Furniture/Material");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
    }

    // Step Three
    private void LoadNewModels()
    {
        GameObject desk = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Desk"));
        desk.name = "Model_0";
        desk.transform.position = new Vector3(0.08f, -0.47f, 7.13f);

        GameObject chair1 = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"));
        chair1.name = "Model_1";
        chair1.transform.position = new Vector3(0.13f, -0.47f, 9.25f);

        GameObject table = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Table"));
        table.name = "Model_2";
        table.transform.position = new Vector3(-2.64, -0.47f, 4.62f);

        GameObject chair2 = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"));
        chair2.name = "Model_3";
        chair2.transform.position = new Vector3(-2.76f, -0.47f, 6.28f);

        GameObject chair3 = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Furniture/Chair"));
        chair3.name = "Model_4";
        chair3.transform.position = new Vector3(-4.37f, -0.47f, 4.81f);
        chair3.transform.rotation = Quaternion.Euler(0f, -97.34f, 0f);
    }

    // Step Four
    private void AddColliders()
    {
        GameObject[] models = new GameObject[5];
        models[0] = GameObject.Find("Model_0");
        models[1] = GameObject.Find("Model_1");
        models[2] = GameObject.Find("Model_2");

public class GameManager : MonoBehaviour

        StepOne();
        StepTwo();
        StepThree();

        StepFive();

    {
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material natureMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");
        Renderer planeRenderer = plane.GetComponent<Renderer>();
        planeRenderer.material = natureMaterial;

    {

public class ObjectController : MonoBehaviour
{
    private void Start()
    {
        // STEP ONE
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");

        // STEP TWO
        for (int i = 0; i < 30; i++)
        {
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find("Model_" + i);
            Destroy(model);
        }

        // STEP THREE
        string[] objectNames = { "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Pine", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Pine", 
                                 "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Pine", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Pine", 
                                 "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Pine", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Pine"};
        
        for (int i = 0; i < objectNames.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject loadedObject = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/" + objectNames[i]);
            Instantiate(loadedObject, GetObjectPosition(i), Quaternion.identity);

using UnityEngine;

public class MySeasonSwitcher : MonoBehaviour
{
    List<GameObject> models = new List<GameObject>();

    // Use this for initialization
    void Start ()
    {
        // Step 1 
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");

        // Step 2
        for(int i = 0; i <= 29; i++)
        {
            string modelName = "Model_" + i;
            GameObject model = GameObject.Find(modelName);
            if(model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }

        // Data for step 3, 4, & 5
        string[] modelTypes = new string[]{ "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Pine", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Pine", 
                                            "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Pine", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Pine", 
                                            "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Pine", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Pine" 
                                          };
        Vector3[] modelPositions = new Vector3[] { new Vector3(-5.761307f,-0.47f,14.48824f), new Vector3(7.368909f,-0.47f,3.656179f), 
                                                   new Vector3(7.60827f,-0.47f,28.15206f), new Vector3(6.845863f,-0.47f,16.70163f) ,
                                                   /* Initialize the rest of the Vector3 array with remaining given positions. */        
                                                 };
        CreateModels(modelTypes, modelPositions);

        // Step 6
        AddColliders();
    }

    void CreateModels(string[] names, Vector3[] positions)
    {
        for(int i = 0; i < names.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject model = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/" + names[i]);
            if(model != null)
            {
                GameObject instance = Instantiate(model, positions[i], Quaternion.identity) as GameObject;
                instance.name = "Model_" + i;
                models.Add(instance);
            }
        }
    }
    
    void AddColliders()
    {
        foreach(GameObject model in models)
        {
            model.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        }
    }
}

            newObject.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        }
    }

    // Start is called before the first frame update
    void Start()
    {
        // STEP ONE
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");

        // STEP TWO
        GameObject[] oldTrees = GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithTag("Tree");

        }

        // STEP THREE

            GameObject newTree = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/" + treeNames[i]));

            // STEP FOUR

            // STEP FIVE

        }

        // STEP SIX
        AddBoxColliderToTrees();
    }

    // STEP SIX
    void AddBoxColliderToTrees()
    {
        GameObject[] allTrees = GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithTag("Tree");
        foreach (GameObject tree in allTrees)
        {
            tree.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        }
    }

 using UnityEngine;
using System.Collections;

public class NatureManager : MonoBehaviour
{
    // STEP ONE: Find the game object called 'Plane' and change its material
    void Start()
    {
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");
    }

    // STEP TWO: Find and destroy all game objects with names starting with "Model_"
    public void DestroyModels()
    {
        GameObject[] models = GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithName("Model_");
        for (int i = 0; i < models.Length; i++)
        {
            Destroy(models[i]);
        }
    }

    // STEP THREE: Instantiate new objects from the Resources/Nature folder
    public void InstantiateModels()
    {
        string[] modelNames = { "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine" };
        for (int i = 0; i < modelNames.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject model = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/" + modelNames[i]));
            model.name = "Model_" + i;
        }
    }

    // STEP FOUR: Rename the freshly created models
    public void RenameModels()
    {
        GameObject[] models = GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithName("Model_");
        for (int i = 0; i < models.Length; i++)
        {
            models[i].name = "Model_" + i;
        }

    // STEP ONE: Find the game object called 'Plane' and change its material
    void Start()
    {
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");
    }

    // STEP TWO: Find and destroy all game objects with names starting with "Model_"
    public void DestroyModels()
    {
        GameObject[] models = GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithName("Model_");
        for (int i = 0; i < models.Length; i++)
        {
            Destroy(models[i]);
        }
    }

    // STEP THREE: Instantiate new objects from the Resources/Nature folder
    public void InstantiateModels()
    {
        string[] modelNames = { "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine" };
        for (int i = 0; i < modelNames.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject model = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/" + modelNames[i]));
            model.name = "Model_" + i;
        }
    }

    // STEP FOUR: Rename the freshly created models
    public void RenameModels()
    {
        GameObject[] models = GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithName("Model_");
        for (int i = 0; i < models.Length; i++)
        {
            models[i].name = "Model_" + i;
        }
    }

    // STEP FIVE: Set the positions of the new objects
    public void SetPositions()
    {
        GameObject[] models = GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithName("Model_");
        models[0].transform.position = new Vector3(6.774252f, -0.47f, 5.32268f);
        models[1].transform.position = new Vector3(4.498785f, -0.47f, 12.07687f);
        models[2].transform.position = new Vector3(-17.50833f, -0.47f, 14.05432f);
        models[3].transform.position = new Vector3(-4.92493f, -0.47f, 4.647117f);
        models[4].transform.position = new Vector3(15.54079f, -0.47f, 9.031234f);
        models[5].transform.position = new Vector3(-12.23363f, -0.47f, 24.07112f);
        models[6].transform.position = new Vector3(-6.285962f, -0.47f, 28.11216f);
        models[7].transform.position = new Vector3(12.85515f, -0.47f, 14.60536f);
        models[8].transform.position = new Vector3(-16.14285f, -0.47f, 22.61144f);
        models[9].transform.position = new Vector3(-9.924309f, -0.47f, 18.90149f);
        models[10].transform.position = new Vector3(-12.36282f, -0.47f, 11.99845f);
        models[11].transform.position = new Vector3(5.891557f, -0.47f, 21.19947f);
        models[12].transform.position = new Vector3(-6.865752f, -0.47f, 24.87579f);
        models[13].transform.position = new Vector3(-14.94092f, -0.47f, 23.08106f);
        models[14].transform.position = new Vector3(5.383296f, -0.47f, 9.281366f);
        models[15].transform.position = new Vector3(-5.330335f, -0.47f, 21.47197f);

        models[17].transform.position = new Vector3(5.401527f, -0.47f, 15.74591f);

        models[19].transform.position = new Vector3(-7.544188f, -0.47f, 9.914202f);
    }

    // STEP SIX: Add a box collider to every object
    public void AddColliders()
    {
        GameObject[] models = GameObject.FindGameObjectsWithName("Model_");
        for (int i = 0; i < models.Length; i++)
        {
            models[i].AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        }
    }

 using UnityEngine;
using System.Collections;

public class Script : MonoBehaviour
{
    // Step ONE: Find the GameObject 'Plane' and change its material
    public void ChangeMaterial()
    {
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material material = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");
            plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = material;
        }
    }

    // Step TWO: Find the GameObjects 'Model_0', 'Model_1', ..., 'Model_4' and destroy them
    public void DestroyModels()
    {
        GameObject model0 = GameObject.Find("Model_0");
        GameObject model1 = GameObject.Find("Model_1");
        GameObject model2 = GameObject.Find("Model_2");
        GameObject model3 = GameObject.Find("Model_3");
        GameObject model4 = GameObject.Find("Model_4");

        if (model0 != null) Destroy(model0);
        if (model1 != null) Destroy(model1);
        if (model2 != null) Destroy(model2);
        if (model3 != null) Destroy(model3);
        if (model4 != null) Destroy(model4);
    }

    // Step THREE: Instantiate the new object loaded from Resources/Naturefolder
    public void InstantiateModels()
    {
        GameObject model0 = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Oak"));
        GameObject model1 = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Oak"));
        GameObject model2 = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Pine"));
        GameObject model3 = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Pine"));
        GameObject model4 = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Wood"));

        // Step FOUR: Rename the freshly created models
        model0.name = "Model_0";
        model1.name = "Model_1";
        model2.name = "Model_2";
        model3.name = "Model_3";
        model4.name = "Model_4";

        // Step FIVE: Set the positions of every object
        model0.transform.position = new Vector3(8.193426f, -0.47f, 19.30498f);
        model1.transform.position = new Vector3(-8.064899f, -0.47f, 2.173819f);
        model2.transform.position = new Vector3(-8.263587f, -0.47f, 20.82765f);
        model3.transform.position = new Vector3(2.913439f, -0.47f, 19.82408f);
        model4.transform.position = new Vector3(-15.17358f, -0.47f, 24.02412f);

        // Step SIX: Add a box collider for every object
        model0.GetComponent<Renderer>().addCollider(new BoxCollider(model0.transform.localScale));
        model1.GetComponent<Renderer>().addCollider(new BoxCollider(model1.transform.localScale));
        model2.GetComponent<Renderer>().addCollider(new BoxCollider(model2.transform.localScale));
        model3.GetComponent<Renderer>().addCollider(new BoxCollider(model3.transform.localScale));
        model4.GetComponent<Renderer>().addCollider(new BoxCollider(model4.transform.localScale));
    }

    {
        ChangeMaterial();
        DestroyModels();
        InstantiateModels();
    }

 using System.Collections;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using UnityEngine;

public class PlaneMaterialChanger : MonoBehaviour
{
    // Step ONE: Find and change the material of the 'Plane' game object.
    private void Start()
    {
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material material = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = material;
    }

    // Step TWO: Destroy the model_0 to model_4 objects.
    private void OnDestroy()
    {
        GameObject model_0 = GameObject.Find("Model_0");
        if (model_0 != null)
            Destroy(model_0);

        GameObject model_1 = GameObject.Find("Model_1");
        if (model_1 != null)
            Destroy(model_1);

        GameObject model_2 = GameObject.Find("Model_2");
        if (model_2 != null)
            Destroy(model_2);

        GameObject model_3 = GameObject.Find("Model_3");
        if (model_3 != null)
            Destroy(model_3);

        GameObject model_4 = GameObject.Find("Model_4");
        if (model_4 != null)
            Destroy(model_4);
    }

    // Step THREE: Instantiate the new objects and load them from Resources/Nature folder.
    private void Start()
    {
        GameObject[] models = new GameObject[] { "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Pine", "Wood" };

        for (int i = 0; i < models.Length; i++)
        {
            string modelName = models[i];
            GameObject obj = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/" + modelName));
            obj.name = "Model_" + i;
        }
    }

    // Step FOUR: Rename the freshly created models with ".name".
    private void Start()
    {
        GameObject[] models = new GameObject[] { GameObject.Find("Model_0"), GameObject.Find("Model_1"), GameObject.Find("Model_2"), GameObject.Find("Model_3"), GameObject.Find("Model_4") };

        for (int i = 0; i < models.Length; i++)
        {
            string modelName = models[i].name;
            if (!modelName.EndsWith(".name"))
                modelName += ".name";
            models[i].name = modelName;
        }
    }

    // Step FIVE: Add positions to every object.
    private void Start()
    {
        GameObject[] models = new GameObject[] { GameObject.Find("Model_0"), GameObject.Find("Model_1"), GameObject.Find("Model_2"), GameObject.Find("Model_3"), GameObject.Find("Model_4") };

        for (int i = 0; i < models.Length; i++)
        {
            Vector3 position = new Vector3(
                -4.086421f, // x
                -0.47f,     // y
                5.742516f   // z
            );

            if (i == 0) position.y += 10f;
            else if (i == 1) position.x += 20f;
            else if (i == 2) position.z += 30f;

            models[i].transform.position = position;
        }
    }

    // Step SIX: Add a box collider to every object.
    private void Start()
    {
        GameObject[] models = new GameObject[] { GameObject.Find("Model_0"), GameObject.Find("Model_1"), GameObject.Find("Model_2"), GameObject.Find("Model_3"), GameObject.Find("Model_4") };

        for (int i = 0; i < models.Length; i++)
        {
            models[i].AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        }
    }

 using System.Collections;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using UnityEngine;

public class ModelChanger : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Step ONE: Find and change material of 'Plane'
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material material = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = material;

        // Step TWO: Destroy old models
        GameObject[] oldModels = new GameObject[] { GameObject.Find("Model_0"), GameObject.Find("Model_1"), GameObject.Find("Model_2"), GameObject.Find("Model_3"), GameObject.Find("Model_4") };
        foreach (GameObject model in oldModels)
        {
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }

        // Step THREE: Instantiate new models
        GameObject[] newModels = new GameObject[] { Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Oak"), Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Oak"), Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Pine"), Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Pine"), Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Wood") };
        foreach (GameObject model in newModels)
        {
            if (model != null)
            {
                // Step FOUR: Rename the freshly created models
                string modelName = model.name.Replace("_", "_").Split('/')[1].ToLower() + ".name";
                model.name = modelName;

                // Step FIVE: Set positions of every object
                Vector3 position;
                switch (modelName.ToLower())
                {
                    case "oak":
                        position = new Vector3(-10.15065f, -0.47f, 22.36088f);
                        break;
                    case "pine":
                        position = new Vector3(11.24331f, -0.47f, 2.437744f);
                        break;
                    default:
                        position = new Vector3(1.362397f, -0.47f, 29.48374f);
                        break;
                }
                model.transform.position = position;

                // Step SIX: Add a box collider for every object
                Collider[] colliders = Physics.OverlapSphere(model.transform.position, 0.5f);
                foreach (Collider collider in colliders)
                {
                    if (collider.gameObject != model)
                    {
                        BoxCollider boxCollider = collider as BoxCollider;
                        if (boxCollider != null)
                        {
                            Destroy(boxCollider);
                        }
                        BoxCollider newBoxCollider = boxCollider as BoxCollider;
                        if (newBoxCollider != null)
                        {
                            model.AddComponent<BoxCollider>().size = new Vector3(0.5f, 0.5f, 0.5f);
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

            {
                oak1.transform.parent = null;

                pine1.transform.parent = oak1.transform.parent;

 using System.Collections;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using UnityEngine;

public class ModelManager : MonoBehaviour
{
    private GameObject plane;

    void Start()
    {
        // Step One: Find the 'Plane' game object and change its material
        plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material material = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = material;
    }

    void StartModelObjects()
    {
        // Step Two: Destroy Model_0 to Model_4
        GameObject[] modelGameObjects = new GameObject[] { GameObject.Find("Model_0"), GameObject.Find("Model_1"), GameObject.Find("Model_2"), GameObject.Find("Model_3"), GameObject.Find("Model_4") };
        foreach (GameObject model in modelGameObjects)
        {
            Destroy(model);
        }

        // Step Three: Instantiate and rename the new objects
        GameObject[] modelTypes = new GameObject[] { Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Oak"), Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Oak"), Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Pine"), Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Pine"), Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Wood") };
        for (int i = 0; i < modelTypes.Length; i++)
        {
            string modelName = "Model_" + (i + 1);
            GameObject newObject = Instantiate(modelTypes[i], GetPosition(i), Quaternion.identity);
            newObject.name = modelName;
        }
    }

    Vector3 GetPosition(int index)
    {
        switch (index)
        {
            case 0:
                return new Vector3(1.21858f, -0.47f, 8.409573f);
            case 1:
                return new Vector3(-14.52545f, -0.47f, 26.36268f);
            case 2:
                return new Vector3(13.0844f, -0.47f, 5.162262f);
            case 3:
                return new Vector3(-10.43456f, -0.47f, 24.50175f);
            case 4:
                return new Vector3(-10.03159f, -0.47f, 22.59448f);
            default:
                throw new Exception("Invalid index");
        }
    }

    void Start()
    {
        StartModelObjects();
    }
}

public class Program : MonoBehaviour

    {

        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = planeMaterial;

        GameObject[] models = new GameObject[] { GameObject.Find("Model_0"), GameObject.Find("Model_1"), GameObject.Find("Model_2"), GameObject.Find("Model_3"), GameObject.Find("Model_4") };

 using System.Collections;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using UnityEngine;

public class Script : MonoBehaviour
{
    // Find the 'Plane' game object and change its material
    void Start()
    {
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material material = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");
            plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = material;
        }
    }

    // Destroy the specified model objects
    void StartDestroyModels()
    {
        GameObject[] modelObjects = new GameObject[4];
        for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++)
        {
            modelObjects[i] = GameObject.Find("Model_" + i.ToString());
            if (modelObjects[i] != null)
            {
                Destroy(modelObjects[i]);
            }
        }
    }

    // Instantiate new objects from the Resources/Nature folder
    void InstantiateModels()
    {
        GameObject[] modelNames = { "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Pine", "Wood" };
        for (int i = 0; i < modelNames.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject modelObject = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/" + modelNames[i]);
            if (modelObject != null)
            {
                // Instantiate the new object
                GameObject instantiatedModel = Instantiate(modelObject);

                // Rename the newly created model with "_name"
                string name = "Model_" + i.ToString() + "_" + modelNames[i].ToLower();
                instantiatedModel.name = name;

                // Set the position of each object
                instantiateModel.transform.position = GetPosition(modelNames[i]);

                // Add a box collider to the model
                BoxCollider boxCollider = instantiatedModel.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            }
        }
    }

    // Function to get the position for each type of model
    Vector3 GetPosition(string modelName)
    {
        switch (modelName.ToLower())
        {
            case "oak":
                return new Vector3(13.90795f, -0.47f, 3.402312f);
            case "pine":
                return new Vector3(14.73408f, -0.47f, 15.08954f);
            case "wood":
                return new Vector3(12.609f, -0.47f, 28.78075f);
            default:
                Debug.LogError("Invalid model name: " + modelName);
                return Vector3.zero;
        }
    }

    void Update()
    {
        StartDestroyModels();
        InstantiateModels();
    }
}

public class PlaneMaterialChanger : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Find the GameObject called 'Plane' and change its material.
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material material = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = material;

        // Find the game objects Model_0 to Model_4 and destroy them.
        GameObject model0 = GameObject.Find("Model_0");
        GameObject model1 = GameObject.Find("Model_1");

        if (model3 != null) Destroy(model3);
        if (model4 != null) Destroy(model4);

        GameObject pine = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Pine"));
        GameObject wood = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Wood"));

        pine.name = "Model_1";
        wood.name = "Model_2";

        oak.transform.position = new Vector3(0.9221921f, -0.47f, 10.10412f);

        pine.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Pine");
        wood.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Wood");

        if (oak != null && oak.GetComponent<BoxCollider>() == null)
        {
            oak.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        }

        if (pine != null && pine.GetComponent<BoxCollider>() == null)
        {
            pine.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        }

        if (wood != null && wood.GetComponent<BoxCollider>() == null)
        {
            wood.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        }
    }

public class Program : MonoBehaviour

    // Step ONE: Find the game object called 'Plane' and change its material.
    void Start()
    {
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
    }

    // Step TWO: Find the game objects that are called Model_0, Model_1, ..., and destroy them.
    void Start()
    {
        GameObject model0 = GameObject.Find("Model_0");
        GameObject model1 = GameObject.Find("Model_1");
        GameObject model2 = GameObject.Find("Model_2");
        GameObject model3 = GameObject.Find("Model_3");
        GameObject model4 = GameObject.Find("Model_4");

        if (model0 != null)
            Destroy(model0);

        if (model1 != null)
            Destroy(model1);

        if (model2 != null)
            Destroy(model2);

        if (model3 != null)
            Destroy(model3);

        if (model4 != null)
            Destroy(model4);

    // Step THREE: Instantiate the new object loaded from the Resources/Naturefolder.

        GameObject wood = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Wood"));

        pine0.name = "Model_1";
        wood.name = "Model_4";

        // Step FOUR: Add a new script to each game object to change its name.
        ChangeName();

        // Instantiate the remaining objects
        GameObject pine1 = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Pine"));
        oak.name = "Model_2";
        pine1.name = "Model_3";

        pine0.name = "Model_4";
    }

    void ChangeName()
    {
        foreach (Transform child in transform)
        {
            if (child.gameObject.CompareTag("BoxCollider"))
                child.gameObject.name += ".name";
        }
    }

    // Step FIVE: Set the positions of every object.
    void Start()
    {
        GameObject model0 = GameObject.Find("Model_0");
        model0.transform.position = new Vector3(-3.648717f, -0.47f, 2.41323f);

 using System.Collections;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using UnityEngine;

public class Script : MonoBehaviour
{
    // Step ONE: Find the 'Plane' gameobject and change its material.
    void Start()
    {
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material material = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");
            plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = material;
        }
        else
        {
            Debug.LogError("The 'Plane' gameobject was not found.");
        }
    }

    // Step TWO: Find and destroy the model gameobjects.
    void Start()
    {
        GameObject[] modelObjects = new GameObject[4];
        for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++)
        {
            string modelName = "Model_" + i.ToString();
            GameObject modelObject = GameObject.Find(modelName);
            if (modelObject != null)
            {
                Destroy(modelObject);
            }
            else
            {
                Debug.LogError("The '" + modelName + "' gameobject was not found.");
            }
        }
    }

    // Step THREE: Instantiate the new objects from Resources/Nature folder.
    void Start()
    {
        GameObject[] modelObjects = new GameObject[5];
        string[] modelNames = { "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Pine", "Wood" };

        for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++)
        {
            GameObject modelObject = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/" + modelNames[i]);
            if (modelObject != null)
            {
                modelObjects[i] = Instantiate(modelObject, GetPosition(i), Quaternion.identity);
            }
            else
            {
                Debug.LogError("The '" + modelNames[i] + "' resource was not found.");
            }
        }

        // Step FOUR: Rename the freshly created models with '.name' suffix.
        for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++)
        {
            string name = "Model_" + i.ToString();
            modelObjects[i].name = name;
        }
    }

    // Get the position for each object based on its type.
    Vector3 GetPosition(int index)
    {
        switch (index)
        {
            case 0:
                return new Vector3(1.479654f, -0.47f, 16.94231f);
            case 1:
                return new Vector3(15.27549f, -0.47f, 27.29271f);
            case 2:
                return new Vector3(-14.05573f, -0.47f, 6.288396f);
            case 3:
                return new Vector3(-8.06697f, -0.47f, 7.136242f);
            case 4:
                return new Vector3(-9.576348f, -0.47f, 19.67951f);
            default:
                return Vector3.zero;
        }
    }

    // Step FIVE: Add a box collider for every object.
    void Start()
    {
        foreach (GameObject modelObject in modelObjects)
        {
            BoxCollider boxCollider = modelObject.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        }
    }
}

 using System.Collections;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using UnityEngine;

public class Script : MonoBehaviour
{
    // Step ONE: Find and change the material of 'Plane'
    private void Start()
    {
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material mat = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");
            plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = mat;
        }
    }

    // Step TWO: Find and destroy the model objects
    private void Start()
    {
        GameObject[] models = new GameObject[] { "Model_0", "Model_1", "Model_2", "Model_3", "Model_4" };

        foreach (string model in models)
        {
            GameObject obj = GameObject.Find(model);
            if (obj != null)
            {
                Destroy(obj);
            }
        }
    }

    // Step THREE: Instantiate new objects
    private void Start()
    {
        GameObject[] objectsToInstantiate = new string[] { "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Pine", "Wood" };

        for (int i = 0; i < objectsToInstantiate.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject obj = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/" + objectsToInstantiate[i]);
            if (obj != null)
            {
                // Step FOUR: Rename the instantiated object
                obj.name = "Model_" + i.ToString();

                // Step FIVE: Set positions of the instantiated object
                obj.transform.position = GetPosition(objectsToInstantiate[i]);

                // Step SIX: Add a box collider to the instantiated object
                obj.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            }
        }
    }

    private Vector3 GetPosition(string type)
    {
        switch (type)
        {
            case "Oak":
                return new Vector3(-7.319811f, -0.47f, 20.39619f);
            case "Pine":
                return new Vector3(-13.44877f, -0.47f, 28.13045f);
            case "Wood":
                return new Vector3(1.992665f, -0.47f, 27.7706f);
            default:
                throw new System.ArgumentOutOfRangeException();
        }
    }

    // Step SIX Alternative: Using Prefab instead of Instantiate
    private void Start()
    {
        GameObject[] objectsToInstantiate = new string[] { "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Pine", "Wood" };

        for (int i = 0; i < objectsToInstantiate.Length; i++)
        {
            GameObject obj = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/" + objectsToInstantiate[i]);
            if (obj != null)
            {
                // Step FOUR: Rename the instantiated object
                obj.name = "Model_" + i.ToString();

                // Step FIVE: Set positions of the instantiated object
                obj.transform.position = GetPosition(objectsToInstantiate[i]);

                // Step SIX: Add a box collider to the instantiated object
                obj.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            }
        }
    }
}
