public class PlaneMaterialChanger : MonoBehaviour
{
    // Find the gameobject called 'Plane' and change its material
    void Start()
    {
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material newMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");

        if (plane != null)
        {
            plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = newMaterial;
        }
        else
        {
            Debug.LogError("Object 'Plane' not found.");
        }
    }

    // Find the gameobjects and destroy them
    void StartDestroy()
    {
        GameObject[] objectsToDestroy = new GameObject[]
        {
            GameObject.Find("Model_0"),
            GameObject.Find("Model_1"),
            GameObject.Find("Model_2"),
            GameObject.Find("Model_3"),
            GameObject.Find("Model_4")
        };

        foreach (GameObject obj in objectsToDestroy)
        {
            if (obj != null)
            {
                Destroy(obj);
            }
        }
    }

    // Instantiate the new object loaded from the Resources/Naturefolder
    void StartInstantiation()
    {
        GameObject[] models = new GameObject[]
        {
            Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Oak"),
            Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Oak"),
            Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Pine"),
            Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Pine"),
            Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Wood")
        };

        {
            // Rename the freshly created models with .name
            string modelName = model.name + "_0";

            // Instantiate the new object and assign its name
            GameObject instantiatedModel = Instantiate(model, Vector3.zero, Quaternion.identity);
            instantiatedModel.name = modelName;

            // Set the position of every object
            switch (modelName)
            {
                case "Model_0":
                    instantiatedModel.transform.position = new Vector3(2.505615f, -0.47f, 6.427849f);
                    break;
                case "Model_1":
                    instantiatedModel.transform.position = new Vector3(7.831707f, -0.47f, 8.979666f);

                    break;
            }

            // Add a box collider for every object
            BoxCollider boxCollider = instantiatedModel.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        }
    }

 using System.Collections;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using UnityEngine;

public class ModelSwitcher : MonoBehaviour
{
    // Step ONE: Find and change the material of the 'Plane' gameobject
    public void ChangeMaterialOfPlane()
    {
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        if (plane != null)
        {
            Material material = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");
            plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = material;
        }
    }

    // Step TWO: Destroy the 'Model_0' to 'Model_4' gameobjects
    public void DestroyModels()
    {
        GameObject[] models = new GameObject[] { GameObject.Find("Model_0"), GameObject.Find("Model_1"), GameObject.Find("Model_2"), GameObject.Find("Model_3"), GameObject.Find("Model_4") };
        foreach (GameObject model in models)
        {
            if (model != null)
            {
                Destroy(model);
            }
        }
    }

    // Step THREE: Instantiate the 'Oak', 'Oak', 'Pine', 'Pine', and 'Wood' gameobjects
    public void InstantiateModels()
    {
        GameObject[] models = new GameObject[] { Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Oak"), Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Oak"), Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Pine"), Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Pine"), Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Wood") };
        for (int i = 0; i < models.Length; i++)
        {
            Instantiate(models[i], GetModelPosition(i));
            models[i].name = $"Model_{i}";
        }
    }

    // Step FOUR: Rename the instantiated models
    private Vector3 GetModelPosition(int modelIndex)
    {
        switch (modelIndex)
        {
            case 0:
                return new Vector3(-16.72869f, -0.47f, 12.44011f);
            case 1:
                return new Vector3(-12.81476f, -0.47f, 25.70001f);
            case 2:
                return new Vector3(-8.525896f, -0.47f, 8.175005f);
            case 3:
                return new Vector3(-5.569391f, -0.47f, 20.93738f);
            case 4:
                return new Vector3(12.98232f, -0.47f, 17.85704f);
            default:
                return Vector3.zero;
        }
    }

    // Step FIVE: Add a box collider to every object
    public void AddBoxColliderToModels()
    {
        GameObject[] models = new GameObject[] { GameObject.Find("Model_0"), GameObject.Find("Model_1"), GameObject.Find("Model_2"), GameObject.Find("Model_3"), GameObject.Find("Model_4") };
        foreach (GameObject model in models)
        {
            if (model != null && !model.GetComponent<BoxCollider>().enabled)
            {
                BoxCollider boxCollider = model.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
                boxCollider.size = new Vector3(1f, 0.01f, 1f);
            }
        }
    }

    private void Start()
    {
        ChangeMaterialOfPlane();
        DestroyModels();
        InstantiateModels();
        AddBoxColliderToModels();
    }
}

        {
            "Oak",
            "Oak",
            "Oak",
            "Oak",
            "Pine",
            "Oak",
            "Oak",
            "Oak",
            "Oak",
            "Pine",
            "Oak",
            "Oak",
            "Oak",
            "Oak",
            "Pine"
        };

        {
            GameObject modelObj = Instantiate(Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/" + modelName), 
                new Vector3(GetRandomFloat(), -0.47f, GetRandomFloat()), Quaternion.identity);
            
            // Rename the freshly created model
            modelObj.name = "Model_" + modelNames.IndexOf(modelName);
            
            // Add a box collider to the model
            BoxCollider boxCollider = modelObj.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        }
    }

    // Helper function to generate random float within a range
    float GetRandomFloat()
    {
        return Random.Range(-20f, 40f); // Adjust the range as needed
    }

    void Start()
    {
        this.StartDestroyingModels();
        this.InstantiateNewModels();
    }

        // Destroy all models with a name that starts with "Model_"

        {
            "Model_0", "Model_1", "Model_2", "Model_3", "Model_4", 
            "Model_5", "Model_6", "Model_7", "Model_8", "Model_9",
            "Model_10", "Model_11", "Model_12", "Model_13", "Model_14"

            Destroy(model);
        }

        // Instantiate the new objects

        {
            "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine",

                Vector3.zero, Quaternion.identity);

            model.transform.position = position;

        // Add a box collider to every object

            string modelName = "Model_" + i.ToString();
            GameObject model = objects[i];
            if (!model.GetComponent<BoxCollider>().enabled)
            {
                BoxCollider boxCollider = model.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
            }
        }

            Instantiate(model10, new Vector3(7.248374f, -0.47f, 16.91367f), Quaternion.identity).name = "Model_10";

        if (model11 != null)
        {
            Instantiate(model11, new Vector3(-4.926936f, -0.47f, 19.86201f), Quaternion.identity).name = "Model_11";
        }
        if (model12 != null)
        {
            Instantiate(model12, new Vector3(1.230484f, -0.47f, 22.8397f), Quaternion.identity).name = "Model_12";
        }
        if (model13 != null)
        {
            Instantiate(model13, new Vector3(-5.386028f, -0.47f, 14.55986f), Quaternion.identity).name = "Model_13";
        }
        if (model14 != null)
        {
            Instantiate(model14, new Vector3(6.935153f, -0.47f, 6.754625f), Quaternion.identity).name = "Model_14";
        }
    }

    // Step FOUR: Add a collider to the instantiated object.
    public void AddCollider(GameObject obj)
    {
        Collider[] colliders = obj.GetComponent<Collider>();
        if (colliders != null && colliders.Length > 0)
        {
            Debug.Log("Collider already added.");
            return;
        }
        BoxCollider boxCollider = obj.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        boxCollider.size = new Vector3(1f, 1f, 1f);
    }

    // Step FIVE: Add a rigidbody to the instantiated object.
    public void AddRigidbody(GameObject obj)
    {
        Rigidbody[] rigidbodies = obj.GetComponent<Rigidbody>();
        if (rigidbodies != null && rigidbodies.Length > 0)
        {
            Debug.Log("Rigidbody already added.");
            return;
        }
        Rigidbody rb = obj.AddComponent<Rigidbody>();
        rb.mass = 1f;
    }

    // Step SIX: Add a material to the instantiated object.
    public void AddMaterial(GameObject obj)
    {
        MeshRenderer[] meshRenderers = obj.GetComponent<MeshRenderer>();
        if (meshRenderers != null && meshRenderers.Length > 0)
        {
            Debug.Log("Material already added.");
            return;
        }
        Material mat = new Material(Shader.Find("Standard"));
        MeshRenderer meshRenderer = obj.AddComponent<MeshRenderer>();
        meshRenderer.material = mat;
    }

    // Step SEVEN: Set the position and rotation of the instantiated object.
    public void SetPositionAndRotation(GameObject obj, Vector3 position, Quaternion rotation)
    {
        obj.transform.position = position;
        obj.transform.rotation = rotation;
    }
}

public class Example : MonoBehaviour
{
    private void Start()
    {
        // Create a new instance of the tree script.
        TreeTreeScript tree = new TreeTreeScript();

        // Instantiate some trees.
        GameObject model0 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Oak");
        GameObject model1 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Pine");
        GameObject model2 = Resources.Load<GameObject>("Nature/Oak");

        tree.InstantiateTree(model0, new Vector3(10f, 10f, 10f), Quaternion.identity);
        tree.InstantiateTree(model1, new Vector3(20f, 20f, 20f), Quaternion.identity);
        tree.InstantiateTree(model2, new Vector3(30f, 30f, 30f), Quaternion.identity);

        // Add colliders and rigidbodies to the instantiated objects.
        tree.AddCollider(model0.transform.parent.gameObject);
        tree.AddRigidbody(model1.transform.parent.gameObject);
        tree.AddCollider(model2.transform.parent.gameObject);

        // Set the position and rotation of the instantiated objects.
        tree.SetPositionAndRotation(model1, new Vector3(10f, 20f, 30f), Quaternion.identity);
    }
}

    public void StartNewModels2()
    {
        GameObject[] models = new GameObject[15];

 using System.Collections;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using UnityEngine;

public class TreeSpawner : MonoBehaviour
{
    // Step ONE: Find the Plane gameobject and change its material
    private void Start()
    {
        GameObject plane = GameObject.Find("Plane");
        Material natureMaterial = Resources.Load<Material>("Nature/Material");
        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = natureMaterial;
    }

    // Step TWO: Destroy all objects with Model_0 to Model_14 names
    private void OnDestroy()
    {
        GameObject[] models = new GameObject[15];
        for (int i = 0; i < 15; i++)
        {
            string modelString = "Model_" + i;
            models[i] = GameObject.Find(modelString);
            Destroy(models[i]);
        }
    }

    // Step THREE: Instantiate the new objects
    private void Start()
    {
        string[] treeTypes = new string[] { "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine" };
        GameObject[] trees = new GameObject[treeTypes.Length];
        for (int i = 0; i < treeTypes.Length; i++)
        {

public class Program : MonoBehaviour

        plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = mat;

    // Step TWO: Destroy the GameObjects

    {
        GameObject[] models = new GameObject[15];

            models[i] = GameObject.Find("Model_" + i);

        }

            plane.GetComponent<Renderer>().material = mat;
        }

            if (obj != null)

            }

        string[] types = { "Oak", "Pine" };
        string[] names = { "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Oak", "Pine" };

                modelObject.name = modelName;

                // Positioning
                Vector3 position;
                switch (modelName)
                {

        {
            return new Vector3(6.244324f, -0.47f, 22.49402f);
        }
        else if (objectType == "Pine")
        {
            return new Vector3(0.726552f, -0.47f, 4.110158f);
        }
        else
        {
            Debug.LogError("Unknown object type");
            return Vector3.zero;
        }
    }

    // Helper function to add a box collider to an object at a given position
    void AddCollider(GameObject obj, Vector3 position)
    {
        BoxCollider cube = obj.AddComponent<BoxCollider>();
        cube.size = new Vector3(1f, 0.5f, 1f);
        cube.offset = new Vector3(position.x, position.y, position.z);
    }

                Instantiate(oak, new Vector3(Instantiate(oak).transform.position.x + Random.Range(-10f, 10f), 1f, Mathf.RoundToInt(Random.Range(100f, 300f))), Quaternion.identity);
            }
            else
            {
                Instantiate(pine, new Vector3(Instantiate(pine).transform.position.x + Random.Range(-10f, 10f), 1f, Mathf.RoundToInt(Random.Range(100f, 300f))), Quaternion.identity);
            }
        }

        }
    }

        StartDestroyModelObjects();
        StartInstantiateModelObjects();

        StartSetModelPositions();
